♪ I'VE GOT A JOB WAITING
FOR MY GRADUATION ♪

08:33.207 --> 08:36.037
♪ 50 THOU A YEAR WILL
BUY A LOT OF BEER ♪

08:36.080 --> 08:38.039
♪ THINGS ARE GOING GREAT ♪

08:38.082 --> 08:40.215
♪ AND THEY'RE ONLY
GETTING BETTER ♪

08:42.433 --> 08:45.394
♪ I'M DOING ALL RIGHT,
GETTING GOOD GRADES ♪

08:45.437 --> 08:47.483
♪ THE FUTURE'S SO BRIGHT ♪

08:47.527 --> 08:50.530
♪ I'VE GOT TO WEAR SHADES ♪

08:50.573 --> 08:52.532
♪ I'VE GOT TO WEAR SHADES ♪

08:52.575 --> 08:53.837
PERFECTION.

08:53.881 --> 08:58.189
♪ Fairy tales can come true ♪

08:58.233 --> 09:00.931
♪ It can happen to you ♪

09:00.975 --> 09:02.629
♪ If you're young at heart... ♪

09:02.672 --> 09:04.065
BOO.

09:04.108 --> 09:06.807
[ laughs ]
OH, IKE.

09:06.850 --> 09:08.939
HI.

09:08.983 --> 09:10.288
'MORNING.

09:10.332 --> 09:11.855
WHERE'S THE NAUGHTY BOY?

09:11.899 --> 09:14.205
IN HIS ROOM.

09:14.249 --> 09:16.207
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
THAT TALK WITH HIM?

09:16.251 --> 09:18.209
YEAH, BUT DON'T EXPECT
ANY MIRACLES.

09:18.253 --> 09:21.386
LOOK, PLEASE DON'T... DON'T LET
HIM KNOW THAT I PUT YOU UP TO IT.

09:21.430 --> 09:23.040
DEAR HEART, RELAX.

09:23.084 --> 09:25.303
WHY DON'T YOU JUST FORGET ABOUT
THAT CRAZY OLD COOT ANYWAY

09:25.347 --> 09:27.175
AND LET ME TAKE YOU AWAY
FROM ALL THIS?

09:27.218 --> 09:29.569
- [ girls rapping ]
- DON'T START RAPPING.

09:29.612 --> 09:31.222
YOU GUYS SUCK
AS RAPPERS.

09:31.266 --> 09:34.617
STOP RAPPING. IT'S OUT.
IT HAPPENED A LONG TIME AGO.

09:34.661 --> 09:37.489
♪ Don't you know that it's worth ♪

09:37.533 --> 09:40.405
♪ Every treasure on earth ♪

09:40.449 --> 09:44.540
♪ To be young at heart? ♪

09:44.584 --> 09:47.238
[ chattering ]

09:47.282 --> 09:49.458
OH, GOD, HERE THEY COME.

09:49.501 --> 09:50.851
OH, DON'T STEP ON THE FLOWERS.

09:50.894 --> 09:52.853
OH, SHIT.
I STEPPED ON THE FLOWERS.

09:52.896 --> 09:54.855
♪ AND THE OTHERS,
THEY THINK WE'RE SO COOL ♪

09:54.898 --> 09:56.596
♪ WE'RE THE COOLEST
GANG YOU EVER CAN... ♪

09:56.639 --> 09:57.727
♪ GO, MAUREEN ♪

09:57.771 --> 10:01.035
♪ GO, GO, GO, MAUREEN ♪

10:01.078 --> 10:04.342
DAMN IT.

10:04.386 --> 10:06.780
[ beat-boxing ]

10:06.823 --> 10:08.564
HOW MANY TIMES
HAVE I TOLD YOU

10:08.608 --> 10:11.088
- THIS IS PRIVATE PROPERTY?
- EVERY DAY, SIR.

10:11.132 --> 10:13.613
WELL, THEN WHY DON'T YOU
GO ANOTHER WAY?

10:13.656 --> 10:17.791
"FOOLISH CONSISTENCY IS THE
HOBGOBLIN OF LITTLE MINDS"...

10:17.834 --> 10:19.793
EMERSON, 1841.

10:19.836 --> 10:22.099
YEAH, LIKE EMERSON, LAKE & PALMER.
I'VE HEARD OF THEM.

10:22.143 --> 10:26.364
OH, STAY OFF THE GRASS.
LOOK WHAT YOU'RE DOING TO MY LAWN.

10:26.408 --> 10:28.410
YOU DON'T HAVE TO THANK US, SIR.
IT WAS OUR PLEASURE.

10:28.453 --> 10:31.543
"THANK YOU"
NEVER ENTERED MY MIND.

10:31.587 --> 10:36.026
YOU KNOW, YOU ARE
DISTURBING MY WORK.

10:36.070 --> 10:39.116
OH, WELL, I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT, SIR...

10:39.160 --> 10:41.815
WE'RE VERY SORRY.

10:41.858 --> 10:44.513
- AND THIS WILL NEVER HAPPEN AGAIN.
- NEVER, EVER.

10:44.556 --> 10:45.688
- NEVER.
- NEVER.

10:45.732 --> 10:49.300
THAT'S WHAT YOU
ALWAYS SAY.

10:49.344 --> 10:51.781
- YOU DO?
- I DON'T.

10:51.825 --> 10:54.958
BUT I'LL TELL YOU WHAT...
THIS WILL BE THE LAST TIME...

10:55.002 --> 10:56.264
- OH.
- WHOA.

10:56.307 --> 10:57.961
- OH, MY GOD.
- OH, MY GOD.

10:58.005 --> 11:00.964
THERE'S THE CRIMSON TIDE.
[ laughs ]

11:01.008 --> 11:02.966
♪ You can laugh when your dreams... ♪

11:03.010 --> 11:05.969
- OH, SHIT.
- ♪ Fall apart at the seams... ♪

11:06.013 --> 11:08.363
[ dance music playing ]

11:13.673 --> 11:15.936
Gena:
WELL, YOU'RE AS BIG A BABY AS THEY ARE.

11:15.979 --> 11:17.938
THEY'RE CHILDREN.
THEY HAVE AN EXCUSE.

11:17.981 --> 11:19.504
WHAT'S YOURS?

11:19.548 --> 11:21.681
Ike:
I TOLD YOU 1,000 TIMES, COLEMAN...

11:21.724 --> 11:23.421
Coleman:
"PUT UP A FENCE." I KNOW.

11:23.465 --> 11:25.685
AND I'VE TOLD YOU
1,000 TIMES IT'S...

11:25.728 --> 11:28.339
Together:
...THE PRINCIPLE...
THEY'VE GOT TO LEARN RESPECT.

11:28.383 --> 11:30.298
- Marge: HI, KIDS.
- Gena: HI, MARGE.

11:30.341 --> 11:33.344
- WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU, IKE?
- DON'T ASK. I'M EMBARRASSED ENOUGH.

11:33.388 --> 11:36.347
I GUESS YOU COULD SAY HE'S KIND
OF RED IN THE FACE, YUCK-YUCK.

11:36.391 --> 11:38.349
YEAH, WELL, YOU'RE GONNA
BE RED IN THE FACE

11:38.393 --> 11:41.178
WHEN YOU GET THE BILL FOR MY
NEW JOGGING SUIT, YUCK-YUCK.

11:41.222 --> 11:42.397
MARGE, HELP US.

11:42.440 --> 11:44.704
OKAY, THAT'S DANISH
AND COFFEE FOR IKE,

11:44.747 --> 11:46.706
BACON AND EGGS
FOR MRS. ETTINGER.

11:46.749 --> 11:49.230
AND WHAT WILL YOU HAVE,
BAD BOY OVER HERE?

11:49.273 --> 11:51.232
THE USUAL...
A CHICKEN SALAD SANDWICH

11:51.275 --> 11:53.234
ON SEVEN-GRAIN TOAST.
HOLD THE CHICKEN...

11:53.277 --> 11:55.802
I KNOW, I KNOW,
BETWEEN MY KNEES.

11:55.845 --> 11:57.238
I CAN'T TAKE
ANY MORE OF THIS.

11:57.281 --> 11:58.848
YOU WANT YOUR RAW
SQUASH OR NOT?

11:58.892 --> 12:01.851
AS WE ALL KNOW, RAW SQUASH
IS EXCELLENT FOR...

12:01.895 --> 12:04.375
IF YOU MAKE ONE REFERENCE
TO BODILY FUNCTIONS

12:04.419 --> 12:06.856
DURING THIS MEAL, I'M GONNA
PUKE ALL OVER THE TABLE.

12:06.900 --> 12:08.902
[ laughter ]

12:28.312 --> 12:31.446
[ laughing ]

12:31.489 --> 12:34.014
WELL, SERIOUSLY,
COLEMAN,

12:34.057 --> 12:36.407
YOU GOTTA SEE IT
THROUGH GENA'S EYES.

12:36.451 --> 12:39.106
I MEAN, YOU GO IN
THAT ROOM FOR HOURS

12:39.149 --> 12:42.500
AND MEDITATE, OR WHATEVER
THE HELL YOU DO,

12:42.544 --> 12:44.415
AND THEN YOU COME OUT AND
START TALKING LIKE A...

12:44.459 --> 12:46.809
...CRAZY MAN, HUH?
IS THAT WHAT SHE SAID?

12:46.853 --> 12:48.811
SHE HOPES YOU'RE CRAZY.

12:48.855 --> 12:50.813
CRAZY CAN BE CURED.
IF IT'S THE OTHER,

12:50.857 --> 12:52.815
THEN THERE'S NOTHING
ANYBODY CAN DO ANYWAY.

12:52.859 --> 12:54.817
LOOK, I'M NOT
GETTING SENILE

12:54.861 --> 12:56.645
AND I'M NOT CRAZY
EITHER.

12:56.688 --> 12:58.125
WELL, WHAT'S SHE WORRIED ABOUT?

12:58.168 --> 13:00.910
THERE MUST BE SOME REASONABLE
EXPLANATION FOR ALL THIS.

13:00.954 --> 13:02.869
IKE,

13:02.912 --> 13:04.871
I AM CONDUCTING

13:04.914 --> 13:07.090
A SCIENTIFIC EXPERIMENT.

13:07.134 --> 13:10.920
NOBODY KNOWS
WHAT DREAMS REALLY ARE.

13:10.964 --> 13:14.271
NOW IF I CAN FIND
THE POINT

13:14.315 --> 13:16.621
WHERE THEY INTERSECT
WITH REALITY

13:16.665 --> 13:20.147
AND ENTER ONE
CONSCIOUSLY,

13:20.190 --> 13:22.976
IF I COULD REALLY ENTER

13:23.019 --> 13:24.978
THE DREAM STATE,

13:25.021 --> 13:28.111
WELL, WHO KNOWS?
MAYBE I COULD LIVE FOREVER.

13:30.548 --> 13:34.204
WELL, JUST BE CAREFUL
WHAT YOU WISH FOR, COLEMAN.

13:35.684 --> 13:39.470
STOP WISHING
FOR IT, PAL.

13:39.514 --> 13:41.429
NO, NO, NO, COME ON,
STOP LOOKING AT HER.

13:41.472 --> 13:42.734
WANT TO GET
YOUR ASS KICKED?

13:42.778 --> 13:44.998
- Bobby: NO.
- THEN STOP LOOKING.

13:45.041 --> 13:46.695
Ike: OH, I CAN'T LOOK
AT THIS.

13:46.738 --> 13:49.480
Gena:
DOES ANY OF THIS MAKE
ANY SENSE TO YOU?

13:49.524 --> 13:51.482
Ike:
WELL, I THINK HE BELIEVES WHAT HE SAYS.

13:51.526 --> 13:53.484
AND I CERTAINLY ADMIRE
HIS CONVICTION.

13:53.528 --> 13:55.486
IT'S NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT.

13:55.530 --> 13:57.837
[ boat horn blows ]

13:57.880 --> 14:00.709
I THINK HE'S GOING TO ASK
ME TO DO IT WITH HIM.

14:00.752 --> 14:02.580
THEN I'D WORRY.

14:02.624 --> 14:04.669
DO ME A FAVOR...

14:04.713 --> 14:07.237
DON'T WORRY.

14:07.281 --> 14:09.457
ALL RIGHT,
IT'S YOUR SCALP.

14:12.025 --> 14:14.462
YOU KNOW, THE ONLY
HAIR YOU LOSE

14:14.505 --> 14:16.638
YOU PULL OUT
YOURSELF, COLEMAN.

14:18.945 --> 14:21.773
YOU'RE TUGGING.
WHAT'S BOTHERING YOU?

14:21.817 --> 14:24.167
SOMETHING'S ALWAYS
BOTHERING YOU

14:24.211 --> 14:26.517
WHEN YOU PULL
AT YOUR LIP.

14:26.561 --> 14:28.998
[ chuckles ]

14:32.045 --> 14:34.003
YOU KNOW,
WHEN TWO PEOPLE

14:34.047 --> 14:36.005
LIVE TOGETHER
FOR 36 YEARS,

14:36.049 --> 14:39.530
THEY DESERVE TO KNOW WHAT THEY
CAN EXPECT FROM ONE ANOTHER.

14:39.574 --> 14:41.968
THAT'S TRUE.

14:42.011 --> 14:45.362
YOU ALWAYS SAID
YOU LIKED ADVENTURE.

14:45.406 --> 14:49.497
OH, BUT THAT WAS TRIPS TO
PENNSYLVANIA, NEW JERSEY.

14:49.540 --> 14:52.021
I'M NOT SO SURE
ABOUT THIS.

14:52.065 --> 14:54.458
OH, THEN WHY DID YOU

14:54.502 --> 14:56.504
PLAY THAT LITTLE GAME
WITH ME TONIGHT?

14:58.898 --> 15:03.206
BECAUSE YOU WANTED TO PACIFY
A FOOLISH OLD MAN?

15:06.383 --> 15:07.732
I DON'T KNOW.

15:13.477 --> 15:17.046
I LOVE YOU,
DEAR WOMAN.

15:17.090 --> 15:20.310
AND I WANT US TO BE
TOGETHER IN THIS LIFE

15:20.354 --> 15:22.922
AS LONG AS NATURE
PERMITS.

15:24.793 --> 15:26.055
THAT'S WHY.

15:26.099 --> 15:28.231
WHAT'S WHY?

15:30.277 --> 15:32.496
BECAUSE YOU'RE
A CHARMER.

15:33.802 --> 15:35.978
WHAT ARE YOU
THINKING ABOUT?

15:36.022 --> 15:37.588
[ light switch clicks ]

15:37.632 --> 15:39.068
OH, DON'T YOU DARE.

15:39.112 --> 15:42.593
TO HELL WITH IT. LET THE GAMES BEGIN.

15:42.637 --> 15:45.466
Bobby:
ONE, TWO, A-ONE, TWO, THREE, AND...

15:45.509 --> 15:47.816
Together:
♪ I'M GONNA WAIT ♪

15:47.859 --> 15:51.298
♪ TILL THE MIDNIGHT HOUR, YEAH ♪

15:51.341 --> 15:55.215
- ♪ WHEN THERE'S NOBODY LEFT AROUND... ♪
- [ chattering ]

15:55.258 --> 15:57.260
Bobby:
THERE'S NOBODY ELSE AROUND... NOBODY.

15:57.304 --> 16:01.003
Together:
♪ I'M GONNA WAIT TILL THE MIDNIGHT HOUR ♪

16:01.047 --> 16:03.005
♪ THE MIDNIGHT HOUR... ♪

16:03.049 --> 16:05.181
[ laughing, chattering ]

16:20.457 --> 16:24.157
♪ NOW I CAN REMEMBER ♪

16:24.200 --> 16:28.117
♪ THE DRESS THAT YOU WORE ♪

16:28.161 --> 16:31.033
♪ BUT I NEVER
REALLY UNDERSTOOD ♪

16:31.077 --> 16:34.645
♪ WHAT ALL THE TEARS WERE FOR ♪

16:34.689 --> 16:38.301
♪ AND YOU LOOKED SO YOUNG ♪

16:38.345 --> 16:42.479
♪ ON THAT SWEET SUMMER MORNING ♪

16:42.523 --> 16:45.482
♪ AND I THOUGHT THAT YOU
WOULD STAY THE SAME ♪

16:45.526 --> 16:48.007
♪ THE WAY YOU WERE BEFORE ♪

16:50.009 --> 16:53.403
♪ I GUESS THOSE DAYS ARE OVER ♪

16:53.447 --> 16:56.841
♪ AND WE CAN NEVER
GET THEM BACK ♪

16:56.885 --> 17:00.628
♪ 'CAUSE TIME RUNS WILD ♪

17:00.671 --> 17:03.935
♪ TIME RUNS FREE ♪

17:03.979 --> 17:06.721
♪ TIME RUNS WILD
LIKE THE CHILD ♪

17:06.763 --> 17:10.377
♪ THAT'S LIVING INSIDE OF ME ♪

17:10.420 --> 17:15.164
♪ OH, NOW I GUESS
WE JUST GOT OLDER ♪

17:15.208 --> 17:17.732
♪ I GUESS WE JUST LOST TRACK ♪

17:17.775 --> 17:21.561
♪ 'CAUSE TIME RUNS WILD ♪

17:21.605 --> 17:25.131
♪ TIME RUNS FREE ♪

17:25.174 --> 17:27.655
♪ TIME RUNS WILD
LIKE THE CHILD ♪

17:27.698 --> 17:30.701
♪ THAT'S LIVING INSIDE OF ME ♪

17:30.745 --> 17:36.098
♪ HEY, TIME RUNS WILD ♪

17:36.142 --> 17:39.449
♪ TIME RUNS FREE ♪

17:39.493 --> 17:42.191
♪ TIME RUNS WILD
LIKE THE CHILD ♪

17:42.235 --> 17:44.889
♪ THAT'S LIVING INSIDE OF ME... ♪

17:44.933 --> 17:47.066
LOOK, MAN, I'M BORED.

17:47.109 --> 17:49.416
FORGET BOBBY AND DINGER.
LET'S GO.

17:49.459 --> 17:51.809
HEY, WOULD YOU RELAX?
THEY'LL BE HERE, ALL RIGHT?

17:51.853 --> 17:54.203
PARENTAL BULLSHIT.

17:54.247 --> 17:55.944
LOOK WHO IT IS.

17:55.987 --> 17:57.946
MUST BE
BAND PRACTICE, HUH?

17:57.989 --> 18:00.209
WHAT'S THE MATTER?
YOU BOYS FORGET YOUR FLUTES?

18:02.559 --> 18:05.258
- MAN, CHECK OUT THE TITS ON THAT ONE.
- HEY, THAT'S MY GIRLFRIEND.

18:05.301 --> 18:07.216
YEAH, I KNOW, JOEL.
WHAT DO YOU THINK ABOUT THAT?

18:07.260 --> 18:09.479
- OH, I THINK YOU'RE AN ASSHOLE, DUMAS.
- THAT'S IT, MAN.

18:09.523 --> 18:11.481
HEY, CHILL OUT, MAN.
TIME AND PLACE.

18:11.525 --> 18:13.483
NOT IN FRONT
OF THE LADIES.

18:13.527 --> 18:15.006
OKAY.

18:15.050 --> 18:18.140
DON'T FORGET TO WRITE,
OKAY, JOEL?

18:18.184 --> 18:19.402
NICE JACKET.

18:19.446 --> 18:22.405
♪ TIME RUNS WILD ♪

18:22.449 --> 18:25.582
♪ TIME RUNS FREE ♪

18:25.626 --> 18:29.282
♪ TIME RUNS WILD LIKE THE CHILD... ♪

18:29.325 --> 18:31.893
YO, KELLER, MAN, WAIT UP.
I CAN ONLY LIMP SO FAST.

18:31.936 --> 18:34.983
YEAH, WELL, YOUR MOM BROKE YOUR LEG.
YOU DEAL WITH IT.

18:35.026 --> 18:37.464
OH, OH, THAT HURTS.

18:37.507 --> 18:39.640
RAGGING ON MY MADRE,
DUDE.

18:43.122 --> 18:45.602
WHAT WAS THAT
ALL ABOUT?

18:45.646 --> 18:48.127
NOTHING NOW.

18:48.170 --> 18:50.129
MAYBE A LITTLE
SOMETHING LATER.

18:50.172 --> 18:52.609
COME ON.

18:52.653 --> 18:56.787
♪ I'M LONGING TO LINGER
TILL DAWN, DEAR ♪

18:56.831 --> 19:00.051
♪ JUST SAYING THIS ♪

19:00.095 --> 19:02.793
♪ SWEET DREAMS TILL
SUNBEAMS FIND YOU... ♪

19:02.837 --> 19:04.143
[ laughing ]

19:04.186 --> 19:08.190
♪ SWEET DREAMS THAT LEAVE
ALL WORRIES BEHIND... ♪

19:08.234 --> 19:11.802
[ laughing ]
COLEMAN.

19:11.846 --> 19:13.369
IT'S TWO BLOCKS.

19:13.413 --> 19:15.371
IT'S A MIRACLE
WE MADE IT HOME.

19:15.415 --> 19:17.634
OH, THAT'S
THE LAST TIME

19:17.678 --> 19:19.636
I EVER HAVE A DRINK
AS LONG AS I LIVE.

19:19.680 --> 19:23.162
THAT'S EASY
FOR YOU TO SAY.

19:23.205 --> 19:25.816
NO, IT'S NOT.
THEY'RE ASSHOLES.

19:25.860 --> 19:27.818
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THEM.

19:27.862 --> 19:30.778
WE'LL CATCH YOU GUYS
LATER.

19:30.821 --> 19:33.302
WHOA, I SAID LATER,
DEREK.

19:38.089 --> 19:40.788
SO, BOBBY, YOUR PARENTS GIVING
YOU SHIT AGAIN OR WHAT?

19:40.831 --> 19:43.094
YEAH, WELL,
YOU KNOW,

19:43.138 --> 19:45.358
WE ALL GOT A JOB
TO DO.

19:45.401 --> 19:47.577
THEY DO THEIRS.
I DO MINE.

19:47.621 --> 19:49.579
YEP, I KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE SAYING, PAL.

19:49.623 --> 19:52.060
THIS THING'S HANDED DOWN
FROM GENERATION TO GENERATION.

19:52.103 --> 19:54.105
IT'S LIKE THIS TRADITIONAL
THING, I THINK.

19:54.149 --> 19:56.630
YOU THINK?
WELL, THERE'S A NEW ONE FOR YOU.

19:56.673 --> 19:58.719
[ both laugh ]

20:00.503 --> 20:03.419
COME ON, JUST HELP ME
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

20:03.463 --> 20:06.509
YOU DID SO WELL
THE FIRST TIME.

20:06.553 --> 20:09.773
OH, COLEMAN,
DON'T SPOIL IT.

20:09.817 --> 20:12.559
WE HAD SUCH
A WONDERFUL DAY.

20:12.602 --> 20:14.082
MY HEAD IS SPINNING.

20:14.125 --> 20:16.432
THAT'S JUST PERFECT...
NO INHIBITIONS.

20:16.476 --> 20:18.869
ALL RIGHT, PROMISE ME,
IF I DO THIS,

20:18.913 --> 20:20.871
THAT YOU'LL NEVER
BRING IT UP EVER AGAIN.

20:20.915 --> 20:22.656
OKAY, I PROMISE.

20:22.699 --> 20:25.702
YOU PROMISE?
WHY SHOULD I?

20:25.746 --> 20:27.269
'CAUSE I LOVE YOU.

20:27.313 --> 20:31.142
I LOVE YOU TOO, BUT I'M
STILL COLD OUT HERE.

20:34.755 --> 20:37.236
WHY CAN'T WE
DO THIS INSIDE?

20:37.279 --> 20:39.890
BECAUSE WE'RE CLOSER
TO NATURE.

20:39.934 --> 20:44.286
- NOW FEEL THE ENERGY OF THE EARTH COME UP...
- [ giggling ]

20:44.330 --> 20:49.073
...THROUGH YOUR LEGS
AND ARMS.

20:49.117 --> 20:51.337
IT FEELS SO GOOD.

20:53.600 --> 20:56.342
BE LIKE THE ROOTS
OF A TREE.

20:56.385 --> 20:58.344
YOU BE LIKE A ROOT.

20:58.387 --> 21:00.346
I FEEL LIKE A SAP.

21:00.389 --> 21:02.348
JUST RELAX.

21:02.391 --> 21:04.350
STOP TELLING ME
TO RELAX.

21:04.393 --> 21:06.787
OKAY, I WON'T.

21:06.830 --> 21:08.919
LET IT FLOW THROUGH YOU.

21:08.963 --> 21:12.401
EXTEND OUT TO MEET IT.

21:12.445 --> 21:15.970
STOP TALKING
AND CLOSE YOUR EYES.

21:18.146 --> 21:22.716
COLEMAN, IT'S WORKING.

21:22.759 --> 21:24.283
- NO, IT'S NOT, JOEL.
- RELAX.

21:24.326 --> 21:26.589
STOP IT.

21:26.633 --> 21:27.938
COME ON.
COME ON, GENIUS.

21:27.982 --> 21:30.071
COME ON, LET'S GO.
COME ON, GOOD BOY.

21:30.114 --> 21:32.769
I'VE GOT WORK TO DO.
I'VE GOT WORK TO DO.
LET'S GO. RUN.

21:32.813 --> 21:35.946
RUN. GO WITH IT.
RUN.

21:35.990 --> 21:39.254
WHY AM I RUNNING?
I HAVE A BROKEN LEG.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.648
♪ WE WERE BORN ♪

21:41.691 --> 21:44.433
♪ BEFORE THE WIND ♪

21:46.174 --> 21:49.177
♪ ALSO YOUNGER THAN THE SUN ♪

21:52.006 --> 21:54.748
♪ 'ERE THE BONNIE BOAT WAS WON ♪

21:54.791 --> 21:57.925
♪ AS WE SAILED INTO THE MYSTIC ♪

22:02.669 --> 22:07.064
♪ HARK NOW, HEAR
THE SAILORS CRY ♪

22:08.675 --> 22:10.633
♪ SMELL THE SEA ♪

22:10.677 --> 22:12.722
♪ AND FEEL THE SKY ♪

22:15.203 --> 22:18.206
♪ LET YOUR SOUL AND SPIRIT FLY ♪

22:18.249 --> 22:20.948
♪ INTO THE MYSTIC ♪

22:26.388 --> 22:29.304
♪ AND WHEN THAT FOGHORN BLOWS ♪

22:30.566 --> 22:32.873
♪ I WILL BE COMING HOME ♪

22:34.527 --> 22:37.617
♪ MM MM ♪

22:37.660 --> 22:41.534
♪ AND WHEN THAT FOGHORN
WHISTLE BLOWS ♪

22:43.057 --> 22:45.059
♪ I GOTTA HEAR IT ♪

22:45.102 --> 22:47.148
♪ I DON'T HAVE TO FEAR IT ♪

22:47.191 --> 22:49.672
♪ AND I ♪

22:49.716 --> 22:52.458
♪ WANT TO ROCK YOUR GYPSY SOUL ♪

22:53.894 --> 22:57.376
♪ JUST LIKE WAY BACK
IN THE DAYS OF OLD ♪

22:59.465 --> 23:02.946
♪ AND TOGETHER WE WILL FLOAT ♪

23:02.990 --> 23:05.035
♪ INTO THE MYSTIC ♪

23:07.603 --> 23:10.476
♪ COME ON, GIRL ♪

23:30.060 --> 23:34.804
♪ TOO LATE TO STOP NOW ♪

23:44.945 --> 23:46.250
WHERE AM I?

23:46.294 --> 23:48.688
OH, GREAT.
TELL HIM HE'S HOME, KIT.

23:48.731 --> 23:51.255
WHO ARE YOU?
WHO'S HE?

23:51.299 --> 23:53.519
WHO'S SHE?
WHERE AM I?

23:53.562 --> 23:56.435
OH, MY LORD,
HE'S GOT AMNESIA.

23:56.478 --> 23:58.698
HEY, BOBBY,
IT'S ME... DINGER.

23:58.741 --> 24:00.439
DON'T YOU KNOW ME?

24:00.482 --> 24:02.441
- WHERE'S GENA?
- WHO'S GENA?

24:02.484 --> 24:04.443
MAYBE HE HAS
A GIRLFRIEND.

24:04.486 --> 24:06.923
NO, MA'AM, HE DOES HAVE A GIRLFRIEND.
HER NAME IS SHELLEY.

24:06.967 --> 24:09.491
- HE HAS A GIRLFRIEND.
- NO, HE DOESN'T HAVE ANY GIRLFRIEND.

24:09.535 --> 24:11.493
I WOULD KNOW ABOUT IT.
HE'S ON DRUGS.

24:11.537 --> 24:13.277
DON'T LOOK AT ME, SIR.
I'M TOTALLY CLEAN.

24:13.321 --> 24:14.844
WHAT... WHAT'S GOING ON?

24:14.888 --> 24:16.106
HE'S MOVING.

24:16.150 --> 24:18.108
YOU'D THINK
I CAN SEE THAT.

24:18.152 --> 24:20.459
OH, MY GOD,
WHERE IS SHE?

24:20.502 --> 24:21.938
WHERE IS WHO SHE?

24:21.982 --> 24:24.245
WHERE'S SHELLEY SHE
OR WHERE IS LAINIE SHE?

24:24.288 --> 24:26.813
- WHO THE HELL IS LAINIE?
- LAINIE'S JOEL'S GIRLFRIEND, SIR.

24:26.856 --> 24:29.468
- WHO'S JOEL?
- WOW, THIS IS WORSE THAN I THOUGHT.

24:29.511 --> 24:31.470
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
HE WAS DATING.

24:31.513 --> 24:33.907
WELL, SHE'S A VERY NICE GIRL, MA'AM.

24:36.213 --> 24:40.087
OH, MY GOD.
I'M HIM.

24:40.130 --> 24:43.003
SHIT!

24:43.046 --> 24:44.526
HELP!

24:44.570 --> 24:46.528
DINGLES, GO AFTER HIM.

24:46.572 --> 24:48.399
IT'S DINGER, SIR. I CAN'T.
I HAVE A BROKEN LEG.

24:48.443 --> 24:50.401
WOULD YOU MOVE?

24:50.445 --> 24:51.925
HE'S DATING.

24:54.275 --> 24:57.321
OH, NO MILK, NO COOKIES...
NOTHING.

24:57.365 --> 25:00.629
♪ WHERE IS SHE? ♪

25:00.673 --> 25:02.152
♪ WHERE IS SHE? ♪

25:02.196 --> 25:04.894
♪ I'VE BEEN LOOKING ♪

25:04.938 --> 25:07.506
♪ NIGHT AND DAWN... ♪

25:07.549 --> 25:09.595
WHAT ARE YOU DOING OVER THERE,
YOU ROTTEN LITTLE BUTT WAD?

25:09.638 --> 25:11.988
HEY, JACK,
IT'S ME... COLE...

25:12.032 --> 25:14.817
GET OUT OF HERE, YOU LITTLE SCUMBAG,
OR I'M GONNA CALL YOUR PARENTS.

25:14.861 --> 25:16.602
WHERE THE HELL
CAN HE BE?

25:16.645 --> 25:18.865
IF SOMETHING HAPPENS
TO HIM, KIT, I'M JUST...

25:18.908 --> 25:20.823
GUS, DO YOU THINK
HE KNOWS WHO WE ARE?

25:20.867 --> 25:23.347
OF COURSE HE KNOWS WHO WE...
WELL, ON THE OTHER HAND...

25:23.391 --> 25:25.219
YOU KNOW, WE'LL GET HIM
THE BEST HELP MONEY CAN BUY.

25:25.262 --> 25:27.003
WE SHOULD HAVE DONE IT
YEARS AGO.

25:27.047 --> 25:29.528
- BOBBY.
- MOM?

25:29.571 --> 25:32.705
HEY, IT'S A START.

25:32.748 --> 25:35.751
CAN I GO TO SLEEP
NOW, PLEASE?

25:35.795 --> 25:40.147
HE MUST HAVE HAD
A VERY TRYING DAY.

25:40.190 --> 25:42.671
WHERE IS MY BEDROOM?

25:45.544 --> 25:47.589
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

25:51.419 --> 25:54.074
♪ WHERE IS SHE? ♪

26:02.430 --> 26:04.388
THAT WAS AMAZING.

26:05.825 --> 26:07.000
WHAT HAPPENED?

26:07.043 --> 26:08.305
GENA,

26:08.349 --> 26:10.699
WHERE WERE YOU?

26:10.743 --> 26:12.745
WITH YOU.

26:14.355 --> 26:15.835
ALWAYS.

26:15.878 --> 26:17.663
BUT I COULDN'T
FIND YOU.

26:17.706 --> 26:19.926
YOU DIDN'T KNOW WHERE TO LOOK.
[ echoing ]

26:19.969 --> 26:22.668
Bobby:
COLEMAN.

26:22.711 --> 26:25.061
HEY, POPS,
WELCOME TO DREAMLAND,

26:25.105 --> 26:27.063
WHERE YOU GET TO LIVE
MY LIFE.

26:27.107 --> 26:29.718
HERE I AM, OVER HERE.
DON'T YOU SEE ME?

26:29.762 --> 26:31.981
- YOU.
- ME.

26:32.025 --> 26:33.069
YOU.

26:33.113 --> 26:34.288
ME.

26:38.553 --> 26:40.860
THIS WASN'T SUPPOSED
TO HAPPEN.

26:40.903 --> 26:43.427
HEY, I WAS JUST MINDING
MY OWN BUSINESS.

26:43.471 --> 26:46.039
SOME SHORTCUTS ARE NOT
WORTH IT THESE DAYS.

26:46.082 --> 26:47.388
YOU'RE TELLING ME.

26:47.431 --> 26:49.259
GET OUT OF HERE
AND DON'T COME BACK.

26:49.303 --> 26:51.087
HEY, JACK, IT'S ME...
COLEMAN.

26:51.131 --> 26:52.915
I THINK HE WAS
TALKING TO ME.

26:52.959 --> 26:55.265
- NOW YOU STAY OUT OF THIS.
- LOOK WHO'S TALKING.

26:55.309 --> 26:56.789
COLEMAN, IS THAT YOU?

26:56.832 --> 27:00.183
WELL, WE'VE ESTABLISHED
OUR BASIC QUESTION.

27:00.227 --> 27:01.881
YOU... ME.

27:01.924 --> 27:07.016
YOU DON'T SEEM TO HAVE
ANY OF THE ANSWERS.

27:07.060 --> 27:09.366
WHAT DO YOUKNOW
ABOUT ALL OF THIS?

27:09.410 --> 27:11.630
SHIT, I'M JUST
CAUGHT IN A DREAM.

27:11.673 --> 27:13.240
AND I DON'T EVEN
THINK IT'S MINE.

27:13.283 --> 27:15.024
WELL, IT CERTAINLY
ISN'T MINE.

27:15.068 --> 27:17.287
WELL, I'M NOT THE ONE WHO WAS
DICKING AROUND WITH REALITY, PAL.

27:17.331 --> 27:19.768
I DON'T CARE ABOUT YOU.
I JUST WANT MY WIFE BACK.

27:19.812 --> 27:22.641
OH, YOU MEAN THAT SWEET,
LOVELY OLD LADY WAS YOUR WIFE?

27:22.684 --> 27:25.252
- THEN YOU'VE SEEN HER?
- OH, YEAH, I SAW HER A FEW MINUTES AGO.

27:25.295 --> 27:26.645
SHE WAS PACKING
SOME THINGS UP.

27:26.688 --> 27:28.908
PACKING?
WHAT? WHY?

27:28.951 --> 27:30.910
WELL, YOU KNOW,

27:30.953 --> 27:32.912
YOU ARE THE BRAINS
AROUND HERE, POPS,

27:32.955 --> 27:35.044
BUT LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING
JUST TO CLUE YOU IN...

27:35.088 --> 27:38.787
WHEN YOU PACK, LEAVING
USUALLY TENDS TO FOLLOW.

27:38.831 --> 27:41.398
- TAKE ME TO HER.
- OH, I CAN'T,

27:41.442 --> 27:44.488
BECAUSE PART OF HER
IS WHERE YOU ARE.

27:44.532 --> 27:46.142
WELL, WHERE AM I?

27:46.186 --> 27:48.231
I DON'T KNOW.

27:48.275 --> 27:50.233
BUT WHEREVER YOU ARE,

27:50.277 --> 27:54.455
WAKE UP SOON, BECAUSE I'M
GONNA BE LATE FOR SCHOOL.

27:54.498 --> 27:57.501
OH, YEAH, POPS, IF YOU
DON'T FIND GENA SOON,

27:57.545 --> 28:00.026
YOU'RE GONNA LOSE
HER FOREVER. HEH!

28:08.469 --> 28:12.212
♪ GOT THE LOOK, GOT THE STYLE ♪

28:12.255 --> 28:16.129
♪ GOT ALL THE MOVES
THAT DRIVE WOMEN WILD... ♪

28:16.172 --> 28:17.608
NO.

28:17.652 --> 28:19.175
THIS WOULD LOOK
BETTER ON IKE.

28:19.219 --> 28:21.700
WHERE THE HELL
DOES THIS KID SHOP?

28:21.743 --> 28:23.963
WHAT...?

28:24.006 --> 28:25.704
AT LEAST HE'S GOT
A GOOD BODY.

28:25.747 --> 28:29.011
OKAY, WHAT DO WE
HAVE HERE? A DUCK.

28:29.055 --> 28:30.709
MAYBE A LITTLE BIT
TOO FLASHY.

28:30.752 --> 28:32.711
WHY DO THEY HAVE
LITTLE CEREAL BOWLS

28:32.754 --> 28:34.669
ROLLED UP AT THE END
OF THEIR SLEEVES?

28:34.713 --> 28:36.889
WHAT THE HELL
IS THIS THING...?

28:40.806 --> 28:44.244
♪ I FIGURED OUT HOW TO GET MY THRILL ♪

28:44.287 --> 28:46.725
- ♪ IF YOU WANT TO KNOCK THEM DEAD... ♪
- AT LEAST I'M NOT THIN.

28:46.768 --> 28:48.596
♪ YOU'VE GOT TO DRESS TO KILL ♪

28:51.730 --> 28:54.384
YOU GUYS AREN'T GONNA
EAT THAT, ARE YOU?

28:54.428 --> 28:56.430
IS HE OKAY?

28:56.473 --> 28:58.432
ASK HIM IF HE WANTS
A POP-TART.

28:58.475 --> 29:00.434
Dinger:
YO, BOBBY, LET'S GO.

29:00.477 --> 29:03.045
TELL HIM
DINGER IS HERE.

29:04.046 --> 29:06.701
I'M SORRY,
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

29:06.745 --> 29:09.008
- GUS.
- GUS. AND...

29:09.051 --> 29:11.227
- MOM.
- MOM.

29:11.271 --> 29:14.622
GUS AND MOM.
WELL, I'LL SEE YOU GUYS LATER.

29:15.884 --> 29:18.669
GUS, I'M GONNA CALL
DR. JORDAN

29:18.713 --> 29:20.976
AND HAVE HIS HEAD...
HAVE HIM LOOK HIM OVER.

29:21.020 --> 29:24.763
I DON'T KNOW. AT LEAST HE'S FINALLY
APPRECIATING THE TIE I GOT HIM.

29:24.806 --> 29:27.591
- [ screaming ]
- OKAY, OKAY.

29:27.635 --> 29:29.593
JUST THE WAY
I LIKE IT.

29:29.637 --> 29:32.640
- OH. OH. THE RUG.
- THAT'S ALL RIGHT. THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

29:32.683 --> 29:35.425
[ imitating guitar riffs ]

29:41.649 --> 29:43.825
WHAT DID YOU DO,
RUN OUT OF MOUSSE?

29:43.869 --> 29:46.088
YOU'RE DINGER, RIGHT?

29:46.132 --> 29:48.090
RIGHT.
ME... DINGER.

29:48.134 --> 29:50.092
YOU... BOBBY.

29:50.136 --> 29:52.486
ME LOOK COOL.
YOU LOOK LIKE SHIT, PAL.

29:52.529 --> 29:53.792
IT'S OKAY, THOUGH.
IT'S OKAY.

29:53.835 --> 29:55.794
WE'LL MAKE IT
A FASHION STATEMENT.

29:55.837 --> 29:57.708
OH, LISTEN, I'VE GOT
SOME THINGS TO DO.

29:57.752 --> 29:59.319
I'LL MEET YOU
AT SCHOOL.

29:59.362 --> 30:02.888
BOBBY, ISN'T THERE ANY FILM
LEFT IN YOUR CAMERA, DUDE?

30:02.931 --> 30:05.368
LOOK, YOU CANNOT CUT
ANY MORE CLASSES.

30:05.412 --> 30:08.284
BOBBY, YOU'RE ALREADY ON
THE BOYS' V.P. MOST-WANTED LIST.

30:08.328 --> 30:10.286
YOU GOTTA GO TO SCHOOL.
IT'S A DIRTY JOB.

30:10.330 --> 30:12.288
SOMEONE'S GOTTA
DO IT, OKAY?

30:12.332 --> 30:14.638
SCHOOL, YOU KNOW,
SCHOOL?

30:14.682 --> 30:15.814
OKAY.

30:15.857 --> 30:18.251
HEY, BUDDY,
SCHOOL'S THAT WAY,

30:18.294 --> 30:19.948
YONDER.

30:19.992 --> 30:22.777
"WE TRAFFIC
IN MOCKERY"...

30:22.821 --> 30:25.171
YEATS, 1928.

30:27.869 --> 30:31.003
OKAY, SURE.
IT'S OKAY, PAL.

30:31.046 --> 30:33.005
I KNOW, I KNOW.
I'VE BEEN THERE.

30:33.048 --> 30:35.007
TAKE A DEEP BREATH.
SHH, IT'S OKAY.

30:35.050 --> 30:37.052
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'M HERE. I'M WITH YOU.

30:37.096 --> 30:40.273
YOU'RE OKAY.
YOU'RE SECURE.

30:40.316 --> 30:43.842
♪ THAT'S GREAT, IT STARTS
WITH AN EARTHQUAKE ♪

30:43.885 --> 30:45.974
♪ BIRDS AND SNAKES, AN AEROPLANE ♪

30:46.018 --> 30:49.499
♪ LENNY BRUCE IS NOT AFRAID... ♪

30:49.543 --> 30:50.979
THAT'S NOT FUNNY,
YOU KNOW.

30:51.023 --> 30:53.155
YOU SHOULD BE PREPARED.
YOU NEED A GOOD EDUCATION.

30:53.199 --> 30:55.114
OH, PREPARE THIS.

30:55.157 --> 30:57.116
HEY, HOW MANY TIMES
HAVE I TOLD YOU

30:57.159 --> 30:58.944
THAT THIS IS
PRIVATE PROPERTY?

30:58.987 --> 31:01.511
BOBBY, YOU'RE STARTING TO SOUND
LIKE THAT OLD MAN. COME ON.

31:01.555 --> 31:04.906
OH, SORRY, I... I JUST WANT
TO SHOW SOME PROPER RESPECT.

31:04.950 --> 31:06.603
OKAY, SURE.
WHAM!

31:06.647 --> 31:09.258
HEY. GOD, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO SMASH THE FLOWERS.

31:09.302 --> 31:11.260
BOBBY, WE ALWAYS
SMASH THE FLOWERS.

31:11.304 --> 31:13.132
IT'S A TRADITION
WITH US, PAL.

31:13.175 --> 31:15.308
GOD DAMN, YOU'RE UPTIGHT.
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME YOU'VE BEEN LAID?

31:15.351 --> 31:16.918
THE OLD MAN...
HE'S GONE.

31:16.962 --> 31:18.833
GOOD. MAYBE HE'S GONE
FOREVER AND EVER.

31:18.877 --> 31:21.009
- WOULD YOU SHUT UP?
- RELAX.

31:21.053 --> 31:23.055
♪ YOU VITRIOLIC, PATRIOTIC, SLAM, FIGHT ♪

31:23.098 --> 31:25.013
♪ BRIGHT LIGHT, FEELING PRETTY PSYCHED... ♪

31:25.057 --> 31:26.928
- WHAT?
- ♪ IT'S THE END OF THE WORLD AS WE KNOW IT... ♪

31:26.972 --> 31:30.192
- OH, MY GOD.
- COME ON. WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

31:30.236 --> 31:33.195
- WELL, A PRETTY CALM DAY.
- ♪ IT'S THE END OF THE WORLD AS WE KNOW IT... ♪

31:33.239 --> 31:37.330
AT LEAST TODAY IT'S CALM.
IT'S A PRETTY CALM DAY. IT'S NICE.

31:37.373 --> 31:39.506
IT'S A JUNGLE.
THEY'RE ANIMALS.

31:39.549 --> 31:41.987
- ♪ I FEEL FINE...
- Bobby: I THINK I'M GONNA BE NAUSEOUS.

31:42.030 --> 31:44.903
- Girl: HEY, WATCH OUT.
- Dinger: WHAT'S WRONG?

31:44.946 --> 31:47.166
- WHERE'S THE LAVATORY?
- THE LAVA-WHAT?

31:47.209 --> 31:49.298
- THE LAVATORY. WHERE'S THE LAVATORY?
- OH, YEAH, YEAH.

31:49.342 --> 31:51.735
UH, IT'S UP THERE...
THE BATHROOM, RIGHT?

31:51.779 --> 31:53.737
OBVIOUSLY.

31:53.781 --> 31:56.392
WELL, WHEN SOME PEOPLE
GOTTA GO, THEY GOTTA GO.

31:56.436 --> 32:00.440
♪ IT'S THE END OF THE WORLD AS WE KNOW IT ♪

32:00.483 --> 32:05.271
♪ IT'S THE END OF THE
WORLD AS WE KNOW IT ♪

32:05.314 --> 32:08.709
♪ IT'S THE END OF THE WORLD AS WE KNOW IT... ♪

32:08.752 --> 32:11.451
HEY, KELLER.

32:11.494 --> 32:12.756
HEY, ASSHOLE,

32:12.800 --> 32:14.976
I HEARD ABOUT YOU BANGING LAINIE LAST NIGHT.

32:15.020 --> 32:17.065
HELLO, KELLER.

32:17.109 --> 32:20.416
KELLER.

32:20.460 --> 32:22.331
YOU BRAIN-DEAD, MAN?

32:22.375 --> 32:24.943
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

32:24.986 --> 32:26.596
[ toilet flushes ]

32:26.640 --> 32:29.121
OH, HE'S BEGGING.
HE'S BEGGING.

32:29.164 --> 32:31.514
WHAT ARE YOU
BEGGING FOR, BOBBY?

32:31.558 --> 32:33.429
ARE YOU LOOKING FOR
A PIECE OF ASS, KELLER?

32:33.473 --> 32:35.954
- THAT IS A SHARP TIE YOU GOT THERE, TONTO.
- THANK YOU.

32:35.997 --> 32:38.173
HEY, BACK OFF,
DUMASS.

32:38.217 --> 32:40.088
THAT'S DUMAS, JOEL.

32:40.132 --> 32:42.003
- YOU KNOW THAT'S FRENCH?
- RIGHT.

32:42.047 --> 32:44.875
YOU MEAN DUMBASS. IT MIGHT BE A
FOREIGN OBJECT, BUT IT AIN'T FRENCH.

32:44.919 --> 32:47.095
[ laughs mockingly ]

32:47.139 --> 32:49.097
BOO.

32:49.141 --> 32:51.099
I WILL REMEMBER THAT,
LITTLE MAN.

32:51.143 --> 32:53.493
HEY, I'M SORRY, GUYS.
I DIDN'T MEAN ANYTHING.

32:55.103 --> 32:57.105
IT'S THE ONLY TIE I HAVE.
I LIKE THE TIE.

32:57.149 --> 32:59.281
- ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
- YEAH, I'M FINE. THANK YOU.

32:59.325 --> 33:01.588
WHAT DID YOU GUYS LEAVE ME IN THERE FOR?
I COULD HAVE GOT MY ASS KICKED.

33:01.631 --> 33:03.459
I DIDN'T, THOUGH.
I WAS BRILLIANT.

33:03.503 --> 33:05.896
WHAA! 'CAUSE I DID
MY KUNG FU SHIT.

33:05.940 --> 33:07.681
I NEED
A STIFF DRINK.

33:09.683 --> 33:11.685
HEY, WANT TO WATCH WHERE
THE HELL YOU'RE GOING?

33:11.728 --> 33:14.122
LAST NIGHT YOU HURT LAINIE.
DO IT AGAIN AND I'LL HURT YOU.

33:14.166 --> 33:16.124
- YOU GOT IT? HUH?
- YEAH.

33:16.168 --> 33:19.084
- THE LEAST YOU CAN DO IS APOLOGIZE, ALL RIGHT?
- I'M SORRY.

33:19.127 --> 33:21.216
AND IF YOU'VE GOT
ANY MOUSSE,

33:21.260 --> 33:24.045
- I WANT YOU TO USE IT.
- OKAY.

33:24.089 --> 33:27.005
- ALL RIGHT.
- ALL RIGHT. THAT WAY?

33:27.048 --> 33:29.529
- APOLOGIZE.
- THAT WAY?

33:35.013 --> 33:37.667
ALL RIGHT, THERE SHE IS.
GO APOLOGIZE.

33:37.711 --> 33:39.713
HER?

33:47.199 --> 33:49.157
UM, EXCUSE ME.

33:49.201 --> 33:51.159
IT'S YOU.

33:51.203 --> 33:52.987
YEAH, MAY I SPEAK
WITH YOU, PLEASE?

33:53.031 --> 33:54.989
- WHAT HAPPENED?
- I'M NOT SURE.

33:55.033 --> 33:56.991
NEITHER AM I.

33:57.035 --> 33:58.601
DO YOU KNOW
WHO I AM?

33:58.645 --> 34:01.300
DO YOU KNOW WHO I AM?

34:01.343 --> 34:04.390
I HOPE SO.
GOD, I HOPE SO.

34:04.433 --> 34:05.913
ME TOO.

34:05.956 --> 34:08.350
GENA, IT ISYOU.

34:08.393 --> 34:10.744
- I'M SO SORRY ABOUT THE ACCIDENT.
- WHO'S GENA?

34:10.786 --> 34:13.485
SO I FIGURED YOU'D BUMP INTO
EACH OTHER SOONER OR LATER.

34:13.529 --> 34:15.966
I'VE GOT TO TALK
TO YOU RIGHT NOW.

34:16.010 --> 34:17.359
WHAT?

34:17.402 --> 34:19.492
NOW HOW ARE YOU GONNA
GET US OUT OF THIS?

34:19.534 --> 34:22.538
I'M A WRECK. I HAD TO GO ALONG WITH
YOU AND YOU HAD TO GET ME INVOLVED.

34:22.581 --> 34:25.889
I'LL GET US OUT OF IT, I SWEAR,
JUST AS LONG AS WE HAVE EACH OTHER.

34:25.933 --> 34:27.456
NO, NO, NO,
THIS ISN'T THE TIME.

34:27.500 --> 34:29.371
BUT, GENA, I'M SO HAPPY
YOU FOUND ME.

34:29.415 --> 34:31.547
GENA?
WHO IS GENA?

34:31.591 --> 34:33.592
WHY DON'T YOU HAVE HER
DO YOUR HOMEWORK?

34:33.636 --> 34:35.116
AND SHE CAN
GET IN TROUBLE

34:35.159 --> 34:37.118
AND YOU CAN TAKE HER
TO THE DANCE ON SATURDAY.

34:37.161 --> 34:40.382
SOME ACCIDENTS AREN'T ACCIDENTS.
THEY'RE BAD KARMA, OKAY?

34:40.426 --> 34:42.384
GOD PUNISHES PEOPLE,
AND DON'T FORGET THAT.

34:42.428 --> 34:44.212
- [ bell ringing ]
- WAIT A MINUTE.

34:44.255 --> 34:47.520
HEY, BUDDY, RELAX. THERE'S PLENTY
OF TIME FOR THAT KIND OF STUFF.

34:47.563 --> 34:49.522
- LET'S GO TO CLASS. COME ON.
- SHIT.

34:49.565 --> 34:51.524
JOEL, BUDDY, CLASS.

34:51.567 --> 34:55.223
HELLO, BOYS.
DON'T SAY HELLO, BOBBY.

34:55.266 --> 34:58.052
PISSING THEM ALL OFF
TODAY, HUH, BOB?

35:09.107 --> 35:11.109
JESUS.

35:21.467 --> 35:23.556
Man:
'MORNING. SIT DOWN, PLEASE.

35:23.599 --> 35:26.036
BOBBY, YOU'RE IN MY SEAT. GET UP.
YOU'RE EMBARRASSING ME.

35:26.080 --> 35:27.995
GET UP. EVERYONE'S WATCHING US. GET UP.

35:30.171 --> 35:32.130
BOBBY, GET AWAY FROM ME.
I JUST DROPPED MY CANE.

35:32.173 --> 35:34.262
YOUR SEAT'S THREE BACK. GO, GO,
YOU'RE MESSING UP. GO, GO.

35:34.306 --> 35:36.960
WHY IS HE BEING
SUCH A DWEEB TODAY?

35:37.004 --> 35:38.962
I DON'T KNOW, MAN,
BUT HE'S MY DWEEB.

35:39.006 --> 35:40.964
HE'S A VERY
WEIRD DWEEB.

35:41.008 --> 35:43.706
ZERO IS
A SIGNIFICANT DIGIT,

35:43.750 --> 35:45.795
FOR IT HAS MEANING.

35:45.839 --> 35:48.755
THE LAST DIGIT WRITTEN
DOWN FOR ANY MEASUREMENT

35:48.798 --> 35:50.626
IS THE UNCERTAIN DIGIT.

35:50.670 --> 35:53.281
ALL NONZERO DIGITS
IN A MEASUREMENT

35:53.325 --> 35:55.283
ARE SIGNIFICANT.

35:55.327 --> 35:56.806
ZEROS ARE OFTEN...

35:56.850 --> 35:58.634
[ bell ringing ]

36:00.680 --> 36:02.290
- MR. KELLER.
- WHAT?

36:02.334 --> 36:04.988
- SIT DOWN.
- I CAN'T RIGHT NOW. I GOTTA GO.

36:05.032 --> 36:06.512
SIT DOWN.

36:06.555 --> 36:08.427
SIR, THIS IS MY I.O.U. HOMEWORK.
I OWE YOU HOMEWORK, SIR.

36:08.470 --> 36:09.950
- THANK YOU, DINGER.
- A LOT OF HOMEWORK, SIR.

36:09.993 --> 36:11.473
- THANKS.
- THANK YOU, SIR.

36:11.517 --> 36:13.606
FIRST, YOU WERE LATE.

36:13.649 --> 36:18.088
NUMBER TWO, THIS WOULD MAKE
A DECENT HALFTIME SCORE.

36:18.132 --> 36:20.656
THAT'S ABOUT IT.
AND YOU'RE NOT STUPID.

36:20.700 --> 36:23.050
SO WHAT SEEMS TO BE
YOUR PROBLEM?

36:23.093 --> 36:25.487
I'M NOT SURE, SIR,
BUT I CAN IMPROVE.

36:25.531 --> 36:27.924
YEAH, AND HOW
WILL YOU DO THAT?

36:27.968 --> 36:29.970
S.A.T.s ARE SATURDAY.

36:30.013 --> 36:33.234
WELL, I MUST TRY HARDER.
I MUST APPLY MYSELF.

36:33.278 --> 36:35.932
I MUST REALIZE THAT "IGNORANCE
IS THE ONLY SLAVERY"...

36:35.976 --> 36:38.500
ROBERT GREEN INGERSOLL,
1876.

36:38.544 --> 36:42.243
♪ IT'S THE END OF THE WORLD AS WE KNOW IT ♪

36:42.287 --> 36:45.290
♪ IT'S THE END OF THE WORLD ♪

36:45.333 --> 36:48.467
♪ AS WE KNOW IT... ♪

36:48.510 --> 36:50.643
KELLER, IT'S REALLY WEIRD
WHEN YOU CAN'T REMEMBER

36:50.686 --> 36:52.688
YOUR OWN
LOCKER COMBINATION.

36:52.732 --> 36:54.690
YEAH.

36:54.734 --> 36:57.954
THERE MUST BE A LOT OF THINGS
YOU DON'T REMEMBER, RIGHT?

36:57.998 --> 37:01.131
LOOK, I MAY NOT BE A GENIUS, BUT
I'M DOING ALL RIGHT IN SCHOOL,

37:01.175 --> 37:03.133
WHICH IS MORE THAN I CAN
SAY FOR SOME PEOPLE.

37:03.177 --> 37:05.135
- THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT.
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

37:05.179 --> 37:07.573
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN
TUGGING YOUR LIP?

37:07.616 --> 37:10.532
I DON'T TUG
ON MY LIP.

37:11.881 --> 37:14.449
- YOU JUST DID.
- SO WHAT?

37:14.493 --> 37:16.451
BOBBY, LOOK, YOU'RE BEING
REALLY WEIRD...

37:16.495 --> 37:19.237
I MEAN, WEIRDER THAN USUAL,
AND THAT'S PRETTY WEIRD.

37:19.280 --> 37:22.196
I JUST WANT TO TALK TO YOU
FOR A MINUTE.

37:22.240 --> 37:23.632
LOOK, I'M GONNA
BE LATE.

37:23.676 --> 37:25.895
NICE COAT.

37:25.939 --> 37:27.767
NICE COAT?
WELL, MAYBE LATER.

37:27.810 --> 37:29.421
YEAH, OKAY,
MAYBE AFTER SCHOOL.

37:29.464 --> 37:31.336
LOOK, CHILL OUT A LITTLE BIT, OKAY?
I GOTTA GO.

37:31.379 --> 37:34.774
OKAY, LET'S GO UP
FOR SOME COMMANDO.

37:38.430 --> 37:41.476
THAT'S RIGHT, MESSING WITH
RAMBO'S LITTLE BROTHER.

37:41.520 --> 37:44.566
THAT'S RIGHT. OH, DUST, PAL, DUST...
FIRST MISTAKE.

37:48.309 --> 37:50.268
NICE TEETH.

37:50.311 --> 37:52.705
[ barks ]
DUDE... OW.

37:52.748 --> 37:55.664
WHY SIT IN GEEK FIELD,
BOBBY?

37:55.708 --> 37:57.666
JUST A LITTLE QUESTION.

37:57.710 --> 38:00.278
A REFRESHING
CHANGE OF PACE, DINGER?

38:00.321 --> 38:02.715
ALL RIGHT, ACCEPTABLE.
IT'S GOOD. IT'S GOOD.

38:02.758 --> 38:05.631
IT'S NOT ONE OF YOUR BEST,
BUT IT'S OKAY, PAL.

38:05.674 --> 38:07.894
THEN AGAIN, WHERE WOULD
BOBBY KELLER BE

38:07.937 --> 38:09.896
WITHOUT A CYNICAL
EAT-SHIT-AND-DIE ATTITUDE

38:09.939 --> 38:12.638
AND SARCASM THAT SHOULD BE
REGISTERED AS A LETHAL WEAPON?

38:12.681 --> 38:15.423
YOU WOULDN'T WANT
TO KNOW.

38:15.467 --> 38:17.860
WHERE ARE YOU THINKING
ABOUT GOING, HARD-ON?

38:17.904 --> 38:20.863
I'M GOING TO HAVE
LUNCH OVER THERE.

38:20.907 --> 38:23.257
AMNESIA STRIKES AT WILL.

38:23.301 --> 38:25.781
YOU KNOW, I SHOULD START CHARGING
YOU A PSYCHIATRIC FEE, MAN.

38:25.825 --> 38:29.742
BOBBY, WE ARE NOT SUPPOSED TO GO
EAT WITH THE GORGEOUS WOMEN...

38:29.785 --> 38:32.135
YOU KNOW, WOMEN?
WE'RE ON PROBATION.

38:32.179 --> 38:34.877
YOU KNOW, BOBBY, PROBATION...
MEN IN CAGES, BOYS IN BONDAGE.

38:34.921 --> 38:37.445
I THINK BOBBY'S SEEING SOMEONE ELSE.
THAT'S WHAT I THINK...

38:37.489 --> 38:39.534
- SOME GIRL NAMED GENA.
- LUCKY BREAK, IF YOU ASK ME.

38:39.578 --> 38:41.536
NO, IT ISN'T,
BECAUSE I REALLY LOVE HIM.

38:41.580 --> 38:43.451
YOU KNOW, I MEAN, HE'S
WEIRD THIS MORNING, BUT...

38:43.495 --> 38:45.627
YEAH, LOOKS LIKE HE KNOWS IT TOO.
HE EXILED HIMSELF TO SLUGVILLE.

38:45.671 --> 38:48.108
- DID YOU SEE HIM WITH THE GEEKS?
- YEAH, I DID.

38:48.151 --> 38:49.283
- LAINIE.
- HUH?

38:49.327 --> 38:50.719
WHAT WERE YOU TALKING
ABOUT THIS MORNING?

38:50.763 --> 38:53.331
UM, HOMEWORK.

38:53.374 --> 38:55.550
NO. WRONG. HUH-UH.
I DO HIS HOMEWORK.

38:55.594 --> 38:56.725
WELL, TENSION.

38:56.769 --> 38:59.772
- HEY, GIRLS.
- HI, GUYS.

38:59.815 --> 39:01.774
HEY, WHOA, JOEL,
WHAT DO YOU GOT IN THERE?

39:01.817 --> 39:04.167
- LET ME HAVE ONE OF THOSE. LET ME HAVE TWO OF THEM.
- OKAY.

39:04.211 --> 39:06.996
ANYTHING ELSE ON THERE?
ALL RIGHT, THANKS A LOT.

39:07.040 --> 39:08.998
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS DOING
IN DORKVILLE?

39:09.042 --> 39:11.784
- WOW, SPEAK OF THE DEVIL.
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY THAT, DINGER?

39:11.827 --> 39:14.352
NOTHING. ME AND BOBBY WERE JUST
TALKING ABOUT EVIL THINGS,

39:14.395 --> 39:16.266
AND YOU GUYS HAPPENED TO SHOW UP.
NOTHING AT ALL.

39:16.310 --> 39:18.181
I'M NOT IN THE MOOD
FOR THIS SHIT, DINGER.

39:18.225 --> 39:21.184
WHAT IS WRONG WITH
EVERYBODY NOWADAYS?

39:21.228 --> 39:23.448
I MEAN, ISN'T THERE ANY LOVE
LEFT IN OUR UNIVERSE, HUH?

39:23.491 --> 39:25.319
Together:
SHUT UP, DINGER.

39:25.363 --> 39:27.408
OH, SHUT UP, DINGER?
REAL MATURE.

39:27.452 --> 39:29.497
- REALLY, REALLY, REALLY MATURE.
- BYE, DINGER.

39:29.541 --> 39:32.195
HEY, BOB, SORRY ABOUT THIS MORNING.
I'M JUST A LITTLE UPTIGHT.

39:32.239 --> 39:34.807
HEY, THAT'S QUITE
ALL RIGHT.

39:34.850 --> 39:36.983
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
CONSUME THAT, ARE YOU?

39:37.026 --> 39:40.595
DON'T YOU REALIZE ALL THE
CHOLESTEROL AND FAT...?

39:40.639 --> 39:43.685
I'M SORRY.
I LIKE BAD BOYS.

40:03.270 --> 40:06.012
♪ I SCREAM, YOU RUN ♪

40:06.055 --> 40:09.407
♪ THIS LOVE'S A HOT GUN ♪

40:09.450 --> 40:12.497
♪ YOU SAY YOU'RE THROUGH ♪

40:12.540 --> 40:15.456
♪ BUT I KNOW IT'S NOT TRUE ♪

40:15.500 --> 40:18.285
♪ DON'T BE SO SURE ♪

40:18.328 --> 40:21.680
♪ THAT YOU DON'T NEED ME ♪

40:21.723 --> 40:25.379
♪ THIS TIME YOU'LL TAKE THE FALL ♪

40:25.423 --> 40:28.861
♪ BABY, BELIEVE ME ♪

40:28.904 --> 40:30.689
♪ YOU'D BETTER WAIT ♪

40:30.732 --> 40:35.215
♪ YOU'LL BE LONELY WHEN I'M GONE ♪

40:35.258 --> 40:37.130
♪ YOU'D BETTER WAIT ♪

40:37.173 --> 40:40.002
♪ YOU'LL BE SAD AND LOST
WHEN YOU FIND OUT ♪

40:40.046 --> 40:43.919
♪ YOU WERE WRONG ♪

40:50.448 --> 40:53.712
♪ DON'T CRY, DON'T WEEP ♪

40:53.755 --> 40:57.106
♪ GOOD LOVE DON'T COME CHEAP ♪

40:57.150 --> 40:59.935
♪ JUST GO, AND YOU'LL SEE ♪

40:59.979 --> 41:02.547
♪ THAT I SAID WHAT I MEAN... ♪

41:02.590 --> 41:04.418
HI, KELLER.

41:04.462 --> 41:06.202
I GUESS I'M NOT
A GOOD DANCER ANYMORE.

41:06.246 --> 41:09.379
LAINIE, LISTEN, I GOTTA TALK TO YOU
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED LAST NIGHT.

41:09.423 --> 41:11.686
YEAH, WE GOTTA STOP
MEETING LIKE THAT.

41:11.730 --> 41:13.601
NO, LAINIE, PLEASE,

41:13.645 --> 41:16.299
YOU GOTTA LISTEN TO ME.
THIS IS IMPORTANT.

41:16.343 --> 41:18.432
LOOK, IT'S OVER.
NO BIG TRAGEDY.

41:18.476 --> 41:19.694
I'M NOT SO SURE
ABOUT THAT.

41:19.738 --> 41:21.391
LOOK, I GOTTA GO
TAKE A SHOWER.

41:21.435 --> 41:24.046
IF YOU REALLY NEED TO TALK TO
ME, COME BY MY HOUSE LATER.

41:31.010 --> 41:32.490
[ both chuckle ]

41:32.533 --> 41:34.492
YOU ALWAYS SEEM
TO FIND ME, DON'T YOU?

41:34.535 --> 41:36.494
WHAT ARE
FRIENDS FOR, HUH?

41:36.537 --> 41:38.147
BEST FRIENDS, RIGHT?

41:38.191 --> 41:40.019
RIGHT ON, MAN.

41:40.062 --> 41:42.412
SINCE I'M YOUR BEST FRIEND,
I'VE GOT A QUESTION FOR YOU.

41:42.456 --> 41:44.414
[ chuckles ]
AND WHAT MIGHT THAT BE?

41:44.458 --> 41:46.808
[ chuckles ]
THAT MIGHT BE, ROBERT,

41:46.852 --> 41:49.332
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU
AND MISS DIAMOND, HUH?

41:49.376 --> 41:52.031
WE'RE JUST FRIENDS.

41:52.074 --> 41:55.338
THAT'S GOOD, YOU KNOW, BECAUSE
JOEL IS REALLY, REALLY CRAZY

41:55.382 --> 41:57.340
ABOUT THAT YOUNG LADY.

41:57.384 --> 41:59.778
YOU KNOW, HE'S ALSO
A LITTLE BIT ON THE EDGE

41:59.821 --> 42:01.780
WHEN IT COMES TO HER,
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

42:01.823 --> 42:03.346
SO IF YOU WANT
TO STAY HEALTHY,

42:03.390 --> 42:05.610
TAKE A LOT, A LOT OF
FLINTSTONES VITAMINS

42:05.653 --> 42:08.526
AND STAY AWAY FROM
LAINIE, OKAY, PLEASE?

42:08.569 --> 42:10.745
OKAY, I'LL KEEP THAT
IN MIND.

42:10.789 --> 42:12.442
THANK YOU.

42:12.486 --> 42:15.968
LISTEN, I'VE GOT SOME
THINGS I HAVE TO DO.

42:16.011 --> 42:18.318
OKAY, LET'S GO DO THEM
TOGETHER, BE A TEAM.

42:18.361 --> 42:20.320
NO, YOU DON'T
UNDERSTAND.

42:20.363 --> 42:22.714
I GOTTA BE ALONE
FOR A WHILE.

42:22.757 --> 42:24.716
SURE.

42:24.759 --> 42:26.587
NO PROBLEM.

42:26.631 --> 42:29.155
NO SKIN OFF MY BACK.
I CAN HANG.

42:31.157 --> 42:33.942
JUST ANOTHER BORING DAY IN THE
COURT FOR ME, THAT'S ALL.

42:33.986 --> 42:36.771
YEP, THAT'S ALL
THAT IS FOR ME.

42:36.815 --> 42:38.730
[ harrumphs ]
LIFE.

42:42.777 --> 42:44.953
[ distant dog barking ]

42:51.917 --> 42:55.050
MY DAUGHTER TELLS ME THERE'S
SOME URGENCY TO YOUR VISIT.

42:55.094 --> 42:57.052
WHAT'VE YOU GOT
FOR ME THIS TIME?

42:57.096 --> 42:59.707
WATER BALLOONS?

42:59.751 --> 43:01.796
IKE, AM I GLAD
TO SEE YOU.

43:01.840 --> 43:04.451
WELL, I'M HAPPY
TO SEE YOU TOO.

43:04.494 --> 43:06.888
AH, BUT YOU'RE GONNA BE
EVEN HAPPIER TO SEE ME

43:06.932 --> 43:08.586
IN A MINUTE.

43:08.629 --> 43:10.849
WELL, I CAN ONLY GET SO
HAPPY, AND THEN I PEAK.

43:10.892 --> 43:12.502
LET'S SIT DOWN.

43:12.546 --> 43:14.896
IKE, LISTEN TO ME.

43:14.940 --> 43:16.898
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO LISTEN TO
WHAT I'M ABOUT TO TELL YOU.

43:16.942 --> 43:20.032
IT'S THE ABSOLUTE TRUTH, BUT
YOU'VE GOT TO BELIEVE ME, OKAY?

43:20.075 --> 43:22.382
YOU HAVE TO USE
ALL YOUR FACULTIES.

43:22.425 --> 43:25.385
YOU HAVE TO BE WILLING TO SUSPEND
YOUR NORMAL PATTERNS OF THINKING.

43:25.428 --> 43:28.170
YOU'VE GOT TO BELIEVE IN
WHAT I'M ABOUT TO SAY.

43:28.214 --> 43:31.739
YOU'RE NOT WORKING WITH THE
YOUNG REPUBLICANS, ARE YOU?

43:31.783 --> 43:35.700
- OH, THIS IS INEFFECTIVE.
- [ chuckles ]

43:35.743 --> 43:39.225
IKE, COME HERE.
COME HERE.

43:40.922 --> 43:42.620
LOOK AT ME.

43:42.663 --> 43:45.274
IKE,

43:45.318 --> 43:48.408
IT'S ME...
YOUR BEST FRIEND

43:48.451 --> 43:50.889
COLEMAN.

43:50.932 --> 43:53.195
COME AGAIN?

43:53.239 --> 43:56.721
GENA AND I TRIED
THE EXPERIMENT,

43:56.764 --> 43:59.245
BUT IT DIDN'T WORK.
SOMETHING HAPPENED,

43:59.288 --> 44:02.074
I DON'T KNOW WHAT, BUT I
GOT TRAPPED IN THIS BODY

44:02.117 --> 44:03.597
AND I CAN'T GET OUT.

44:03.641 --> 44:05.468
CALL THE HOUSE.

44:05.512 --> 44:07.296
I'M NOT THERE.
I'M HERE.

44:07.340 --> 44:09.298
AND I HAD THIS DREAM.
IT WAS...

44:09.342 --> 44:13.085
NOW WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU HAVEN'T DONE ANYTHING

44:13.128 --> 44:14.695
TO MY FRIENDS,
HAVE YOU?

44:14.739 --> 44:19.613
OH, GOD, YOU'RE NOT
LISTENING TO ME.

44:19.657 --> 44:22.703
I'M TIRED.

44:22.747 --> 44:24.836
I'VE HAD A LONG DAY
AT SCHOOL.

44:24.879 --> 44:27.795
[ chuckles ]
WHERE'S COLEMAN?

44:27.839 --> 44:30.406
HE PUT YOU UP TO THIS,
DIDN'T HE?

44:30.450 --> 44:33.105
[ sighs ]
IKE, REMEMBER WHAT
OSCAR WILDE SAID

44:33.148 --> 44:35.585
ABOUT A CYNIC, 1892?

44:35.629 --> 44:38.153
"NONE OF THIS IS FOLDEROL."

44:38.197 --> 44:40.373
WOULD I KNOW THIS?
WATCH.

44:48.947 --> 44:51.471
COLEMAN COULD HAVE
SHOWED YOU THAT.

44:51.514 --> 44:53.473
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

44:53.516 --> 44:56.041
REMEMBER THAT STORY YOU TOLD ME ABOUT
THE TWO DANCING FILIPINO GIRLS

44:56.084 --> 44:58.043
ON YOUR FIRST SHORE
LEAVE IN MANILA?

44:58.086 --> 45:00.262
I NEVER BELIEVED YOU,
RIGHT?

45:03.178 --> 45:06.399
- IT'S A TRUE STORY.
- IKE, I'M WILLING TO BELIEVE YOU,

45:06.442 --> 45:09.532
BUT YOU'VE GOT TO BE
WILLING TO BELIEVE ME.

45:09.576 --> 45:11.186
SMUDGE.
CAREFUL, HE BITES.

45:11.230 --> 45:13.449
SMUDGE, SMUDGE,
COME HERE, COME HERE.

45:13.493 --> 45:17.192
COME HERE, COME HERE,
COME HERE, COME HERE.

45:17.236 --> 45:20.239
- HI, SHEILA.
- HOW DID YOU KNOW MY NAME?

45:20.282 --> 45:22.154
I TOLD HIM.

45:22.197 --> 45:24.156
OH. YOU KNOW,
IT'S AMAZING.

45:24.199 --> 45:26.114
THAT DOG
HATES EVERYBODY.

45:28.943 --> 45:31.119
EXCEPT COLEMAN.

45:33.643 --> 45:35.994
- DON'T YOU THINK YOU'RE OVERREACTING?
- NO, I DON'T.

45:36.037 --> 45:38.692
WHY DO YOU ALWAYS THINK YOU'RE
SUPPOSED TO GIVE IN TO A MAN?

45:38.736 --> 45:40.912
LOOK WHERE IT GOT YOU.

45:43.305 --> 45:45.351
I DIDN'T DO SO BADLY.
WHAT'S WRONG WITH ALL THIS?

45:45.394 --> 45:49.268
MOM, YOU DID EVERYTHING
TO PLEASE DADDY.

45:49.311 --> 45:51.531
SO WHAT DID HE DO?
HE TOOK YOU FOR GRANTED

45:51.574 --> 45:53.533
AND LEFT YOU
FOR SOMEBODY ELSE.

45:53.576 --> 45:56.710
APPARENTLY
IT WASN'T ENOUGH.

45:56.754 --> 45:58.886
I COULD HAVE BEEN
A LITTLE WARMER.

46:02.194 --> 46:04.805
ALL I KNOW IS JOEL'S ONE OF THE FEW BOYS IN THIS TOWN WITH A REAL FUTURE.

46:04.849 --> 46:06.764
HIS PARENTS ARE
DOING QUITE WELL.

46:06.807 --> 46:08.243
HE'S A LITTLE ROUGH
AROUND THE EDGES,

46:08.287 --> 46:09.810
BUT HE'S SMART AND HE'LL
GO ON TO COLLEGE.

46:09.854 --> 46:11.333
MOM, I'M IN
HIGH SCHOOL.

46:11.377 --> 46:13.292
SO JOEL'S TERRIFIC, BUT
IS THAT ANY REASON TO...?

46:13.335 --> 46:16.512
TO WHAT? DON'T PUT
WORDS IN MY MOUTH.

46:16.556 --> 46:17.818
[ knocks ]

46:17.862 --> 46:20.560
NO, JUST THOUGHTS
IN MY HEAD.

46:20.603 --> 46:23.084
DON'T TURN YOUR BACK
ON ME, YOUNG LADY.

46:25.695 --> 46:27.915
- HI, KELLER.
- HELLO, LAINIE.

46:27.959 --> 46:29.917
DO YOU HAVE TIME
TO TALK?

46:29.961 --> 46:31.527
WELL, BOBBY,

46:31.571 --> 46:33.703
IT'S A SHAME YOU DIDN'T
KNOCK SOME SENSE INTO HER.

46:33.747 --> 46:35.705
HI, MISS DIAMOND.

46:35.749 --> 46:37.533
BOBBY, I'M NOT
IN A VERY GOOD MOOD.

46:37.577 --> 46:39.361
IN THAT CASE, MAYBE
YOU SHOULD COME BACK

46:39.405 --> 46:41.363
WHEN HER TEENAGE YEARS
ARE OVER.

46:41.407 --> 46:43.017
WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE GOING?

46:43.061 --> 46:45.063
TO RUN AWAY FROM HOME
AND BECOME A PROSTITUTE.

46:45.106 --> 46:46.804
OH, THEN THIS
MUST BE YOUR...

46:46.847 --> 46:48.631
MOTHER, DON'T.

46:48.675 --> 46:50.720
BYE, MISS DIAMOND.

46:52.810 --> 46:54.681
HEY, I WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR DOING THIS.

46:54.724 --> 46:56.596
ANYTHING TO GET AWAY
FROM MY MOTHER.

46:56.639 --> 46:58.163
GEE, THANKS.
I'M FLATTERED.

46:58.206 --> 46:59.860
THAT WAS SARCASTIC?

46:59.904 --> 47:01.862
NO, I'M JUST TRYING
TO BE MYSELF.

47:03.733 --> 47:07.302
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU WANTED TO TALK.

47:07.346 --> 47:10.001
COME ON, I WANT
TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

47:16.311 --> 47:20.533
♪ WHERE IS SHE? WHERE IS SHE? ♪

47:20.576 --> 47:23.101
♪ I'VE BEEN LOOKING ♪

47:23.144 --> 47:25.016
♪ NIGHT AND DAWN... ♪

47:25.059 --> 47:27.018
WHAT ARE WE DOING?

47:27.061 --> 47:28.715
WE'RE GOING
INSIDE THE HOUSE.

47:28.758 --> 47:30.499
I'M NOT GOING
IN THERE.

47:30.543 --> 47:32.501
WHY NOT? COME ON.
THERE'S NOBODY HOME.

47:32.545 --> 47:34.503
BOBBY, ARE YOU GONNA
HIT ME AGAIN?

47:34.547 --> 47:36.505
NO, I'M NOT GONNA
HIT YOU AGAIN.

47:36.549 --> 47:37.680
COME ON.

47:37.724 --> 47:39.334
NO WAY.

47:39.378 --> 47:41.336
CHICKEN.

47:41.380 --> 47:42.990
♪ WHERE IS SHE? ♪

47:43.034 --> 47:45.645
♪ I'VE BEEN SEARCHING ♪

47:45.688 --> 47:48.909
♪ ON AND ON ♪

47:51.042 --> 47:53.827
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- GETTING SOME REAL FOOD.

47:53.871 --> 47:55.829
EWW, BOBBY,
THAT'S COLD TOFU.

47:55.873 --> 47:57.831
MM, I KNOW. IT'S SO GOOD. WANT SOME?

47:57.875 --> 48:00.225
NO. WHAT ARE WE
DOING HERE?

48:00.268 --> 48:02.314
AND WHY DO YOU
HAVE THE KEY?

48:02.357 --> 48:05.230
I'M WATCHING THE HOUSE
FOR THE OLD PEOPLE,

48:05.273 --> 48:07.232
YOU KNOW, FEEDING THEIR
DOG AND STUFF.

48:07.275 --> 48:09.538
THEY ASKED ME TO, WHILE
THEY'RE OUT OF TOWN.

48:09.582 --> 48:12.019
BESIDES, I THINK IT'S
A NICE PLACE TO COME,

48:12.063 --> 48:14.152
TO GET AWAY FROM MY PARENTS.
I THINK IT'S NEAT.

48:14.195 --> 48:15.762
I THINK IT SMELLS
LIKE OLD PEOPLE.

48:15.805 --> 48:17.503
Lainie:
IT'S SPOOKY.

48:17.546 --> 48:19.505
SPOOKY?
WHERE DO YOU SEE SPOOKY?

48:19.548 --> 48:21.376
NOW COME IN HERE.
I WANT TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

48:21.420 --> 48:23.248
- IT'S IMPORTANT.
- OKAY, OKAY.

48:23.291 --> 48:26.904
WELL, THE OLD GUY ALWAYS HAS
SOME NONSENSE WRITTEN HERE.

48:26.947 --> 48:28.644
THAT'S SWEET.

48:28.688 --> 48:30.646
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT IS SWEET.

48:30.690 --> 48:32.648
BUT IT'S USUALLY
A BUNCH OF BULLSHIT

48:32.692 --> 48:35.434
ABOUT ENERGY
AND YOUTH.

48:35.477 --> 48:36.914
SEEMS HARMLESS.

48:37.958 --> 48:41.657
[ "Young at Heart" playing ]

48:41.701 --> 48:43.964
♪ Fairy tales can come true... ♪

48:44.008 --> 48:45.966
- I LOVE THIS SONG.
- ♪ It can happen to you...

48:46.010 --> 48:47.968
YEAH.

48:48.012 --> 48:49.970
- I KNOW.
- ♪ If you're young at heart... ♪

48:50.014 --> 48:52.538
I CAN'T REMEMBER
WHERE I'VE HEARD IT.

48:52.581 --> 48:54.018
DANCE WITH ME.

48:54.061 --> 48:57.195
♪ For it's hard, you will find ♪

48:57.238 --> 48:59.762
♪ To be narrow of mind ♪

48:59.806 --> 49:03.810
♪ If you're young at heart... ♪

49:05.768 --> 49:07.466
SHE'S VERY BEAUTIFUL.

49:07.509 --> 49:09.381
MM, SO ARE YOU.

49:09.424 --> 49:11.731
♪ With impossible schemes ♪

49:11.774 --> 49:14.777
♪ You can laugh when your dreams ♪

49:14.821 --> 49:17.955
♪ Fall apart at the seams... ♪

49:17.998 --> 49:19.957
LAINIE.

49:21.132 --> 49:23.482
GOOD GOING, COLEMAN.

49:45.983 --> 49:48.420
[ phone rings ]

49:48.463 --> 49:50.465
HELLO.

49:50.509 --> 49:51.989
OH, HI, JOEL.

49:52.032 --> 49:54.295
I REALLY CAN'T TALK
RIGHT NOW, OKAY?

49:54.339 --> 49:56.167
GOOD NIGHT.
SWEET DREAMS.

49:58.343 --> 50:02.260
OH, NO, IT'S YOU.

50:02.303 --> 50:05.393
YOU WERE EXPECTING
MAYBE FREDDY KRUEGER?

50:05.437 --> 50:07.004
WHO'S FREDDY KRUEGER?

50:07.047 --> 50:08.527
IT'S BEFORE YOUR TIME.

50:08.570 --> 50:11.312
LISTEN, WHY DON'T YOU
DO ME A FAVOR

50:11.356 --> 50:13.140
AND STAY OUT OF MY LIFE,
ALL RIGHT, POPS?

50:13.184 --> 50:15.186
NOTHING WOULD GIVE ME
GREATER PLEASURE.

50:15.229 --> 50:17.710
WHERE'S GENA?
AND DON'T CALL ME "POPS."

50:17.753 --> 50:20.800
GENA'S IN THE HOUSE, POPS.

50:25.631 --> 50:27.676
DON'T TRY THE DOOR.
IT'S LOCKED.

50:27.720 --> 50:29.678
- I'VE GOT A KEY.
- IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

50:29.722 --> 50:31.463
- [ rings bell ]
- THIS IS A DREAM.

50:31.506 --> 50:33.682
YOU WANT TO SEE HER...
GO LOOK IN THE WINDOW.

50:35.945 --> 50:37.817
GENA.

50:37.860 --> 50:40.211
GENA, GENA.

50:45.868 --> 50:48.132
WHY DOESN'T SHE
REMEMBER ME?

50:48.175 --> 50:51.787
WELL, THE WAY I SEE IT
IS THAT SHE WASN'T

50:51.831 --> 50:54.051
AS INTO THIS LITTLE
EXPERIMENT AS YOU WERE.

50:54.094 --> 50:58.011
YOU WOULDN'T BY ANY CHANCE
KNOW HOW TO SWITCH US BACK?

50:58.055 --> 51:00.666
ABSOLUTELY.

51:00.709 --> 51:03.669
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
IT JUST SO HAPPENS

51:03.712 --> 51:06.933
TO BE ONE OF THE VERY FIRST
THINGS THAT I LEARNED ABOUT.

51:06.976 --> 51:09.414
WELL, THEN LET'S
DO IT NOW.

51:09.457 --> 51:11.416
- HUH-UH.
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN, HUH-UH?

51:11.459 --> 51:14.332
WELL, WHICH ONE DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND...
HUH OR UH?

51:14.375 --> 51:16.334
THE WHOLE IDEA.

51:16.377 --> 51:18.858
YOU SEE,
I LIKE IT HERE.

51:18.901 --> 51:22.166
IT'S...
WELL, IT'S DREAMY.

51:22.209 --> 51:24.168
IF YOU CATCH MY DRIFT.
HA HA.

51:24.211 --> 51:26.866
DON'T YOU WANT TO GET BACK
TO YOUR OWN LIFE?

51:26.909 --> 51:28.694
NO, I DON'T,
AS A MATTER OF FACT.

51:28.737 --> 51:30.348
SEE, YOU DON'T
UNDERSTAND.

51:30.391 --> 51:33.699
MY PARENTS HATE ME.
I'M FLUNKING EVERY GRADE IN SCHOOL.

51:33.742 --> 51:36.267
DUMAS WANTS TO KICK MY ASS.
AND IF JOEL FOUND OUT

51:36.310 --> 51:38.530
HOW I FEEL ABOUT LAINIE, HE'D
WANT TO KICK MY ASS TOO.

51:38.573 --> 51:40.880
"SHOW ME A MAN WHO HAS
ENJOYED HIS SCHOOL DAYS

51:40.923 --> 51:42.708
AND I'LL SHOW YOU
A BULLY AND A BORE"...

51:42.751 --> 51:44.710
ROBERT MORLEY, 1958.

51:44.753 --> 51:48.061
UP YOURS AND THE HORSE
YOU RODE IN ON.

51:48.105 --> 51:50.542
THAT ISN'T A HORSE.
THAT'S A SHEEP.

51:50.585 --> 51:52.544
WHERE DID IT
COME FROM?

51:52.587 --> 51:55.024
A SHEEP?
I DON'T KNOW.

51:55.068 --> 51:57.244
BUT THIS IS YOUR
SICK DREAM,

51:57.288 --> 51:59.203
AND I'LL TELL YOU ONE THING...
YOU HAVE SOME

51:59.246 --> 52:01.379
DEEP-SEATED PSYCHOLOGICAL
PROBLEMS, MAN.

52:01.422 --> 52:04.643
AND BY THE WAY,
I'M NOT GOING BACK.

52:06.384 --> 52:08.299
WHAT IF I FIXED
EVERYTHING?

52:08.342 --> 52:10.214
OH, AND HOW ARE YOU
GONNA DO THAT, POPS?

52:10.257 --> 52:12.216
DON'T CALL ME "POPS."

52:12.259 --> 52:13.956
I CAN DO IT.

52:14.000 --> 52:17.177
I'VE GOT TO.

52:17.221 --> 52:19.919
WELL, YOU'D BETTER
WORK FAST,

52:19.962 --> 52:22.182
BECAUSE THEY'RE WORKING FAST.

52:22.226 --> 52:25.011
- NOT AS FAST AS I CAN.
- ALL RIGHT, FINE.

52:25.054 --> 52:27.013
BUT JUST DON'T LET JOEL
FIND OUT ABOUT IT,

52:27.056 --> 52:29.015
OR HE'S GONNA "TEAR
YOUR PLAYHOUSE DOWN"...

52:29.058 --> 52:31.409
PAUL YOUNG, 1986.
SEE HOW ANNOYING THAT IS?

52:31.452 --> 52:33.367
ANYWAY, YOU GOTTA DO ME
SOME THINGS.

52:33.411 --> 52:35.239
YOU GOTTA STOP EATING
THE TOFU SHIT,

52:35.282 --> 52:37.676
BECAUSE THE TOFU SHIT
IS DRIVING ME CRAZY.

52:37.719 --> 52:39.504
IT'S MAKING ME
REALLY NAUSEOUS.

52:39.547 --> 52:41.767
AND, YOU KNOW, YOU GOTTA STOP
TELLING PEOPLE WHAT TO EAT.

52:41.810 --> 52:43.769
IT'S JUST NOT LIKE ME.
HOW OFTEN DO YOU SEE ME

52:43.812 --> 52:45.640
TELLING PEOPLE WHAT TO EAT?
I DON'T DO IT.

52:45.684 --> 52:48.643
OKAY, SOMETHING ELSE...
THERE'S SOME HOME MOVIES DOWNSTAIRS.

52:48.687 --> 52:51.646
WATCH THEM. LEARN HOW TO
SPEAK LIKE A NORMAL PERSON.

52:51.690 --> 52:54.606
I DON'T TALK LIKE THAT.
OH, ALSO SOME MOUSSE...

52:54.649 --> 52:57.086
THERE'S SOME MOUSSE IN THE BATHROOM.
YOU GOTTA USE THE MOUSSE.

52:57.130 --> 52:59.045
YOU GOTTA DO SOMETHING WITH MY HAIR.
MY HAIR LOOKS LIKE SHIT.

52:59.088 --> 53:01.961
I NEVER HAVE MY HAIR LOOK LIKE SHIT.
THEY'RE GONNA KNOW SOMETHING'S UP,

53:02.004 --> 53:04.746
SOMETHING'S WEIRD HERE. ALL
RIGHT, OH, ONE LAST THING...

53:04.790 --> 53:06.313
WAKE UP.

53:08.924 --> 53:12.928
OR "YOU'RE GONNA LOSE THAT GIRL"...
BEATLES, 1965. HEH.

53:25.637 --> 53:28.553
"BOBBY'S 16th BIRTHDAY."

54:15.121 --> 54:16.470
HEY, BABE,

54:16.514 --> 54:18.690
I JUST WANTED TO FILL YOU
IN REGARDING LAST NIGHT:

54:18.733 --> 54:21.519
I WANTED TO TELL YOU THAT I
WAS NOT A COOL DUDE, RIGHT?

54:21.562 --> 54:24.348
AND ALSO, LIKE,
I WAS TOTALLY UNCHILLED

54:24.391 --> 54:28.134
AND, YOU KNOW, I SHOULD REALLY
CHILL OUT SOME MORE. RIGHT? RIGHT?

54:28.177 --> 54:30.267
WHY CAN'T YOU SPEAK
LIKE A NORMAL PERSON?

54:30.310 --> 54:32.225
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THEY DON'T HAVE A DOG.

54:32.269 --> 54:34.923
THEY NEVER HAD A DOG.
I DON'T APPRECIATE YOU HITTING ON ME

54:34.967 --> 54:37.361
AND I DON'T THINK YOUR BEST FRIEND WOULD EITHER.
SO WHY DON'T YOU GO AWAY?

54:37.404 --> 54:40.494
LAINIE, I DON'T THINK YOU SEE
WHAT I'M TRYING TO DO HERE.

54:40.538 --> 54:43.323
I JUST WANT TO BE
FRIENDS WITH YOU.

54:43.367 --> 54:45.760
I WANT YOU TO GET
TO KNOW ME AS A PERSON.

54:45.804 --> 54:47.893
ALL YOU KNOW ME IS,
IS KELLER.

54:47.936 --> 54:50.025
I THOUGHT I KNEW YOU,
BOBBY, OKAY?

54:50.069 --> 54:51.592
AND I DO LIKE YOU,
BUT NOT IN THAT WAY.

54:51.636 --> 54:53.464
OKAY, FINE.

54:53.507 --> 54:56.554
WILL YOU DO ME A FAVOR AND MEET ME
AFTER SCHOOL IN A PUBLIC PLACE?

54:56.597 --> 54:58.904
I DON'T THINK SO,
OKAY?

54:58.947 --> 55:00.645
OKAY.

55:00.688 --> 55:02.690
[ bell ringing ]

55:22.667 --> 55:26.148
♪ I'VE GOT DREAMS ♪

55:26.192 --> 55:27.976
♪ DREAMS ♪

55:28.020 --> 55:30.892
♪ TO REMEMBER ♪

55:32.981 --> 55:36.028
♪ I'VE GOT DREAMS ♪

55:36.071 --> 55:38.030
♪ DREAMS... ♪

55:38.073 --> 55:40.119
AREN'T YOU GONNA SAY
SOMETHING STUPID, KELLER?

55:40.162 --> 55:42.295
WHY DO YOU ALWAYS BOTHER ME?
I DON'T EVEN KNOW YOU.

55:42.339 --> 55:43.992
HOW DUMB DO YOU
THINK I AM?

55:44.036 --> 55:45.820
THAT'S A PRETTY LEADING QUESTION.
HOW DUMB ARE YOU?

55:45.864 --> 55:47.648
HUT!

55:50.042 --> 55:53.480
♪ ANOTHER MAN'S ARMS HOLDING YOU TIGHT ♪

55:55.308 --> 55:59.356
♪ NOBODY KNOWS WHAT I FEEL INSIDE ♪

55:59.399 --> 56:02.576
♪ ALL I KNOW, I WALKED AWAY AND CRIED ♪

56:02.620 --> 56:05.187
♪ I'VE GOT DREAMS ♪

56:05.231 --> 56:07.320
♪ DREAMS ♪

56:07.364 --> 56:10.149
♪ TO REMEMBER ♪

56:10.192 --> 56:12.151
♪ LISTEN TO ME ♪

56:12.194 --> 56:15.546
♪ I'VE GOT DREAMS, ROUGH DREAMS ♪

56:15.589 --> 56:17.548
♪ DREAMS TO REMEMBER... ♪

56:17.591 --> 56:19.550
Cheerleaders:
FIGHT, FIGHT, FIGHT!

56:19.593 --> 56:21.508
HEY, HEY, BACK UP, DUMBASS.

56:24.946 --> 56:26.905
ANYBODY ELSE?

56:26.948 --> 56:28.733
YEAH.

56:28.776 --> 56:30.865
- [ laughter ]
- ME.

56:34.216 --> 56:36.001
BREAK IT UP, GUYS.
KELLER.

56:36.044 --> 56:37.176
COME HERE.

56:37.219 --> 56:38.786
HEY, WHAT YOU GOT?

56:38.830 --> 56:40.788
BY THE TIME I FINISH
DOING LAPS,

56:40.832 --> 56:42.311
I'LL BE IN
GRADUATE SCHOOL, DUDE.

56:42.355 --> 56:44.313
RAZOR-SHARP, KELLER,
RAZOR-SHARP.

56:44.357 --> 56:46.315
HEY, WHERE DID YOU LEARN
TO FIGHT LIKE THAT?

56:46.359 --> 56:48.840
UH, KUNG FU
THEATER, DUDE.

56:48.883 --> 56:51.538
- DUDE, STOP SAYING "DUDE," ALL RIGHT?
- OKAY.

56:51.582 --> 56:53.540
- HAVE YOU POONED SHELLEY YET?
- POONED?

56:53.584 --> 56:55.412
YOU KNOW,
SLEPT WITH HER.

56:55.455 --> 56:58.023
OH, YEAH, THAT...
I DON'T THINK SO.

56:58.066 --> 57:00.678
LOOK, MAN,
I HEAR YOU.

57:00.721 --> 57:03.071
I MEAN, NOW BETWEEN
ME AND YOU,

57:03.115 --> 57:05.509
IT'S LIKE LAINIE'S NOT BEING
TOO COOPERATIVE LATELY.

57:05.552 --> 57:09.469
WELL, MAYBE I'M NOT THE RIGHT
GUY TO TALK TO ABOUT THIS.

57:09.513 --> 57:11.732
WHO AM I GONNA
TALK TO... DINGER?

57:11.776 --> 57:15.083
UM, OKAY,

57:15.127 --> 57:17.521
WELL, MAYBE
YOU'RE NOT HER TYPE.

57:17.564 --> 57:19.523
I'M EVERY GIRL'S TYPE.

57:19.566 --> 57:21.699
I MEAN, JESUS, EVEN
HER MOTHER LIKES ME.

57:21.742 --> 57:23.527
IT'S DRIVING ME CRAZY,
YOU KNOW.

57:23.570 --> 57:24.876
IT'S LIKE I CAN'T
UNDERSTAND.

57:24.919 --> 57:26.878
ANY OTHER GIRL
IN THE CLASS... BOOM.

57:26.921 --> 57:29.446
BUT LAINIE... I CAN'T
FIGURE HER OUT.

57:29.489 --> 57:33.101
LISTEN, WHY DON'T YOU
JUST LEAVE HER ALONE?

57:33.145 --> 57:35.539
I MEAN, WHY CAN'T YOU
JUST POON ANOTHER GIRL?

57:35.582 --> 57:38.193
I MEAN, YOU DON'T CARE FOR HER
AND YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND HER.

57:38.237 --> 57:40.195
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO YOU,
KELLER, HUH?

57:40.239 --> 57:42.459
IF WE WEREN'T FRIENDS FOR
SO LONG, I'D KNOCK YOU OUT.

57:42.502 --> 57:43.938
YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

57:43.982 --> 57:46.637
YEAH, YEAH,
I UNDERSTAND THAT.

57:48.334 --> 57:50.292
SORRY.
IT JUST HURT.

57:50.336 --> 57:52.294
OKAY.

57:52.338 --> 57:54.296
- ALL RIGHT?
- ALL RIGHT.

57:54.340 --> 57:55.776
- SORRY.
- DUDE.

57:55.820 --> 57:56.995
DUDE.

58:03.958 --> 58:08.659
♪ Stars fading ♪

58:08.702 --> 58:14.099
♪ But I linger on ♪

58:15.143 --> 58:18.146
♪ Still craving ♪

58:18.190 --> 58:21.933
♪ Your kiss ♪

58:21.976 --> 58:26.285
♪ And I'm longing ♪

58:26.328 --> 58:28.287
♪ To linger ♪

58:28.330 --> 58:31.638
♪ Till dawn ♪

58:31.682 --> 58:34.598
♪ So dream ♪

58:34.641 --> 58:37.818
♪ A little dream ♪

58:37.862 --> 58:43.041
♪ Of me ♪

58:43.084 --> 58:44.869
HEY!

58:47.262 --> 58:49.264
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

58:52.224 --> 58:56.663
♪ Stars shining bright above you ♪

58:56.707 --> 58:59.013
♪ Night breezes seem to whisper ♪

58:59.057 --> 59:01.015
♪ "I love you" ♪

59:01.059 --> 59:04.410
♪ Birds singing in the sycamore tree ♪

59:04.453 --> 59:07.631
♪ Dream a little dream of me ♪

59:09.197 --> 59:13.375
♪ Just say good night and kiss me ♪

59:13.419 --> 59:15.769
♪ Just hold me tight and tell me ♪

59:15.813 --> 59:17.597
♪ You'll miss me ♪

59:17.641 --> 59:21.253
♪ While I'm alone and blue as can be ♪

59:21.296 --> 59:24.212
♪ Dream a little dream of me ♪

59:25.866 --> 59:30.349
♪ Stars fading, but I linger on ♪

59:30.392 --> 59:34.440
♪ Still craving your kiss ♪

59:34.483 --> 59:38.618
♪ And I'm longing to linger till dawn ♪

59:38.662 --> 59:41.578
♪ Just saying this ♪

59:43.057 --> 59:46.844
♪ Sweet dreams till sunbeams find you ♪

59:46.887 --> 59:51.283
♪ Sweet dreams that leave all worries behind you ♪

59:51.326 --> 59:54.852
♪ But in your dreams, whatever they be ♪

59:54.895 --> 59:59.117
♪ Dream a little dream of me, yeah ♪

01:00:16.308 --> 01:00:20.704
♪ Stars fading, but I linger on ♪

01:00:20.747 --> 01:00:24.577
♪ Still craving your kiss ♪

01:00:24.621 --> 01:00:29.451
♪ And I'm longing to linger till dawn ♪

01:00:29.495 --> 01:00:32.933
♪ Just saying this ♪

01:00:32.977 --> 01:00:37.808
♪ Sweet dreams till sunbeams find you ♪

01:00:37.851 --> 01:00:41.855
♪ Sweet dreams that leave all worries behind you ♪

01:00:41.899 --> 01:00:45.467
♪ But in your dreams, whatever they be ♪

01:00:45.511 --> 01:00:49.384
♪ Dream a little dream of me ♪

01:00:49.428 --> 01:00:51.648
YOU'RE CRAZY.
DID YOU KNOW THAT?

01:00:51.691 --> 01:00:54.651
AND I'M ALSO CUTE TOO,
AREN'T I?

01:00:55.782 --> 01:00:59.264
SO WILL YOU
COME GO WITH ME?

01:00:59.307 --> 01:01:01.919
DO I HAVE A CHOICE?

01:01:01.962 --> 01:01:03.964
NO.

01:01:05.487 --> 01:01:07.402
SO HOW DO YOU WANT
TO START THIS?

01:01:07.446 --> 01:01:09.056
HAVE YOU EVER BEEN
HERE BEFORE?

01:01:09.100 --> 01:01:11.145
OF COURSE NOT.
WE'RE THE ONLY ONES HERE UNDER 50.

01:01:11.189 --> 01:01:14.671
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU
AND OLD PEOPLE ANYWAY?

01:01:14.714 --> 01:01:16.455
I'M GONNA TELL YOU
THE TRUTH ABOUT THAT.

01:01:16.498 --> 01:01:18.109
WELL, THAT'LL BE
A FIRST.

01:01:18.152 --> 01:01:20.241
HOW DO YOU KNOW?
WE HARDLY EVER TALK TO EACH OTHER.

01:01:20.285 --> 01:01:22.461
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M SORRY. THAT'S NOT FAIR.

01:01:22.504 --> 01:01:25.116
NO, YOU'RE RIGHT.
WE NEVER DID TALK TO EACH OTHER BEFORE.

01:01:25.159 --> 01:01:27.814
ALL OF A SUDDEN
YOU'VE CHANGED.

01:01:27.858 --> 01:01:30.643
WHY?

01:01:30.687 --> 01:01:32.993
IT'S NOT IMPORTANT.
LISTEN,

01:01:33.037 --> 01:01:35.126
SOMETHING HAPPENED
TO THOSE OLD PEOPLE.

01:01:35.169 --> 01:01:37.694
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
WHERE ARE THEY ANYWAY?

01:01:37.737 --> 01:01:40.784
I DON'T KNOW.
EVER SINCE YOU AND I HAD OUR ACCIDENT,

01:01:40.827 --> 01:01:42.786
THEY HAVEN'T
BEEN THERE.

01:01:42.829 --> 01:01:46.137
IT'S LIKE THEY'RE GONE.
AND I'M REALLY WORRIED ABOUT THEM.

01:01:46.180 --> 01:01:47.747
THAT'S PRETTY WEIRD,
HUH?

01:01:47.791 --> 01:01:49.749
YEAH, LIKE YOU.

01:01:49.793 --> 01:01:52.056
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA HAVE?
I HAVEN'T GOT ALL DAY.

01:01:52.099 --> 01:01:54.145
HI, MARGE.
LADIES FIRST.

01:01:54.188 --> 01:01:56.016
DO YOU HAVE
A RAW VEGETABLE PLATE?

01:01:56.060 --> 01:01:57.583
WHAT MADE YOU
ORDER THAT?

01:01:57.626 --> 01:01:59.367
I'M ON A DIET.
DO YOU?

01:01:59.411 --> 01:02:01.630
ALL I'VE GOT IS THE REST OF THE
SQUASH WE KEEP FOR MR. ETTINGER.

01:02:01.674 --> 01:02:03.894
YOU WANT SOME SEVEN-GRAIN
BREAD WITH THAT?

01:02:03.937 --> 01:02:05.417
WE'VE GOT LOTS
OF THAT TOO.

01:02:05.460 --> 01:02:07.811
[ hums "Twilight Zone" theme ]

01:02:07.854 --> 01:02:10.857
OKAY, LISTEN, IF I TAKE
YOU SOMEPLACE ELSE

01:02:10.901 --> 01:02:12.859
WHERE NOTHING WEIRD
HAPPENS,

01:02:12.903 --> 01:02:15.296
WILL YOU COME
WITH ME?

01:02:15.340 --> 01:02:18.038
- PUBLIC OR PRIVATE?
- YOUR CHOICE.

01:02:20.258 --> 01:02:23.696
♪ OH, 'CAUSE I WAS YOUNG
AND EAGER TO SEE ♪

01:02:23.740 --> 01:02:26.264
♪ WHAT LIFE WAS ALL ABOUT ♪

01:02:27.831 --> 01:02:32.357
♪ OH, NOW I GUESS
WE JUST GOT OLDER ♪

01:02:32.400 --> 01:02:34.663
♪ I GUESS WE JUST LOST TRACK ♪

01:02:34.707 --> 01:02:38.755
♪ 'CAUSE TIME RUNS WILD ♪

01:02:38.798 --> 01:02:41.235
♪ TIME RUNS FREE ♪

01:02:42.497 --> 01:02:44.761
♪ TIME RUNS WILD
LIKE THE CHILD ♪

01:02:44.804 --> 01:02:48.373
♪ THAT'S LIVING INSIDE OF ME ♪

01:02:48.416 --> 01:02:53.247
♪ HEY, TIME RUNS WILD ♪

01:02:53.291 --> 01:02:56.947
♪ TIME RUNS FREE ♪

01:02:56.990 --> 01:02:59.427
♪ TIME RUNS WILD
LIKE THE CHILD ♪

01:02:59.471 --> 01:03:02.517
♪ THAT'S LIVING INSIDE OF ME ♪

01:03:06.086 --> 01:03:10.047
♪ OH, IN THE DARK
OF NIGHT I PRAY ♪

01:03:10.090 --> 01:03:13.746
♪ WELL, DID I THROW
MY YOUTH AWAY ♪

01:03:13.790 --> 01:03:16.749
♪ ON A DREAM I'LL
NEVER REALIZE... ♪

01:03:16.793 --> 01:03:18.229
SO MY DAD LEFT

01:03:18.272 --> 01:03:20.231
AND MY BROTHER CHOSE
TO LIVE WITH HIM...

01:03:20.274 --> 01:03:22.233
MALE BONDING
AND THAT STUFF.

01:03:22.276 --> 01:03:24.235
NOW IT'S JUST
ME AND MY MOM.

01:03:24.278 --> 01:03:26.237
AND YOU'VE MET HER.

01:03:26.280 --> 01:03:28.413
ANYWAY, JOEL GAVE ME
A LOT OF ATTENTION

01:03:28.456 --> 01:03:30.894
WHEN I NEEDED IT.

01:03:30.937 --> 01:03:33.331
WHY AM I TELLING YOU
MY LIFE'S STORY?

01:03:33.374 --> 01:03:36.116
BECAUSE I'M A GOOD
LISTENER.

01:03:36.160 --> 01:03:38.118
YEAH, YOU ARE.

01:03:38.162 --> 01:03:40.120
SO YOUR DAD LET YOU
BORROW HIS CAR?

01:03:40.164 --> 01:03:41.687
I THINK IT'S NEAT.

01:03:41.730 --> 01:03:43.428
YEAH.
NOW WHAT ABOUT JOEL?

01:03:43.471 --> 01:03:44.951
DO YOU LOVE HIM?

01:03:44.995 --> 01:03:46.953
I'M IN HIGH SCHOOL.
WHO CARES?

01:03:46.997 --> 01:03:49.782
- YOU DIDN'T ANSWER MY QUESTION.
- I'M JUST A KID.

01:03:49.826 --> 01:03:52.872
YOU STILL DIDN'T
ANSWER MY QUESTION.

01:03:52.916 --> 01:03:54.526
WHAT ELSE
DO I HAVE TO DO?

01:03:54.569 --> 01:03:57.268
KISS.

01:04:11.238 --> 01:04:13.284
I FEEL SO SAFE
WITH YOU.

01:04:13.327 --> 01:04:15.547
I FEEL LIKE I CAN
TELL YOU ANYTHING.

01:04:15.590 --> 01:04:17.027
I KNOW.

01:04:17.070 --> 01:04:19.072
WHY?

01:04:22.989 --> 01:04:24.512
BECAUSE WE'RE THEM.

01:04:24.556 --> 01:04:26.514
WE'RE WHO?

01:04:26.558 --> 01:04:27.994
[ sighs ]

01:04:28.038 --> 01:04:30.823
WE'RE THE OLD COUPLE.
YOU'RE GENA AND I'M COLEMAN.

01:04:30.867 --> 01:04:33.478
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?
YOU'RE SPOILING EVERYTHING.

01:04:33.521 --> 01:04:36.481
IT'S THE TRUTH.
YOU'VE GOT TO HEAR ME, PLEASE.

01:04:36.524 --> 01:04:39.484
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR YOU. I'M STARTING
TO LIKE YOU. I DON'T WANT TO HEAR THIS.

01:04:39.527 --> 01:04:41.442
- BUT YOU'VE GOT TO. IT'S THE TRUTH.
- BOBBY.

01:04:41.486 --> 01:04:43.357
- LISTEN TO ME.
- WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

01:04:43.401 --> 01:04:44.968
- YOU WERE RIDING YOUR BIKE AND I WAS RUNNING, OKAY?
- OH, MY GOD.

01:04:45.011 --> 01:04:47.187
- AND...
- BOBBY KELLER, YOU'RE A JERK...

01:04:47.231 --> 01:04:48.362
A REAL JERK.

01:04:48.406 --> 01:04:50.364
NO, LAINIE,
I'M JUST DOING THIS

01:04:50.408 --> 01:04:52.366
BECAUSE I WANTED TO LIVE
A LONGER LIFE WITH YOU.

01:04:52.410 --> 01:04:54.978
COME ON.
GENA, COME BACK.

01:04:55.021 --> 01:04:58.111
[ loud music playing ]

01:04:58.155 --> 01:05:01.158
MY FAULT.
YOU ARE IN THE WRONG PLACE, BOBBY BOY.

01:05:01.201 --> 01:05:02.376
OH, MY GOD.

01:05:02.420 --> 01:05:05.510
SO NOW IT'S JUST YOU
AND ME AND MY BOYS.

01:05:05.553 --> 01:05:07.338
- LAINIE!
- BOBBY!

01:05:07.381 --> 01:05:08.861
I DON'T GIVE A SHIT
ABOUT THAT.

01:05:08.905 --> 01:05:10.950
AND I DON'T GIVE
A SHIT ABOUT YOU.

01:05:10.994 --> 01:05:12.778
STOP IT!

01:05:14.867 --> 01:05:17.914
STOP IT. STOP IT.
YOU'RE KILLING HIM.

01:05:24.094 --> 01:05:26.052
NAH,

01:05:26.096 --> 01:05:28.925
I THINK I'D RATHER
JACK OFF.

01:05:28.968 --> 01:05:30.839
AND YOU...

01:05:30.883 --> 01:05:33.581
YOU'RE GONNA LOOK REALLY
GOOD FOR THE DANCE, CUPCAKE.

01:05:33.625 --> 01:05:34.756
BOBBY.

01:05:34.800 --> 01:05:36.758
LET'S GO, DUDE.

01:05:36.802 --> 01:05:39.979
BOBBY, ARE YOU OKAY?

01:05:40.023 --> 01:05:42.286
ARE YOU OKAY?

01:05:42.329 --> 01:05:44.375
OH, MY GOD.

01:05:50.076 --> 01:05:52.078
OH, MY GOD.

01:05:58.955 --> 01:06:02.088
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR A FRIGHTENING,

01:06:02.132 --> 01:06:04.569
CONFUSING, STRANGE
AND DANGEROUS TIME.

01:06:04.612 --> 01:06:08.007
WHAT MORE COULD
A GIRL ASK FOR?

01:06:08.051 --> 01:06:11.141
I FEEL LIKE I SHOULD
APOLOGIZE TO YOU,

01:06:11.184 --> 01:06:15.232
BUT I TOLD
THE TRUTH.

01:06:15.275 --> 01:06:18.452
BOBBY, I REALLY
LIKE YOU,

01:06:18.496 --> 01:06:21.064
BUT I CAN'T BELIEVE A STORY LIKE THIS.
IT'S JUST NOT FAIR.

01:06:21.107 --> 01:06:24.067
YOU'RE RIGHT.
YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT ISN'T FAIR.

01:06:24.110 --> 01:06:28.071
YOU SHOULD LET YOUR MOTHER
TAKE A LOOK AT THAT EYE.

01:06:28.114 --> 01:06:30.769
LISTEN, CAN YOU
DO ME A FAVOR?

01:06:30.812 --> 01:06:34.903
WHEN YOU DREAM TONIGHT,
REMEMBER IT FOR ME.

01:06:34.947 --> 01:06:37.384
WHY? AM I GONNA DREAM
THAT WE'RE MARRIED?

01:06:37.428 --> 01:06:39.386
I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW.

01:06:39.430 --> 01:06:42.041
MAYBE I'M CRAZY.
MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

01:06:42.085 --> 01:06:45.218
AND IF I AM, I NEED
SOME SERIOUS HELP.

01:06:45.262 --> 01:06:48.091
BUT IF I'M NOT,

01:06:48.134 --> 01:06:51.616
YOU'VE GOT TO REMEMBER
THIS DREAM, PLEASE.

01:06:51.659 --> 01:06:54.227
JUST DO IT FOR ME, PLEASE.

01:06:54.271 --> 01:06:55.663
PLEASE.

01:06:55.707 --> 01:06:58.405
I GOTTA GO.
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

01:07:03.671 --> 01:07:06.109
DEAD MEAT.
DEAD MEAT.

01:07:06.152 --> 01:07:08.633
WE'RE GONNA KILL
DUMAS FOR THIS.

01:07:08.676 --> 01:07:11.636
- HEY, BE CAREFUL.
- DON'T TOUCH ME.

01:07:13.290 --> 01:07:15.944
- HI, MISS DIAMOND.
- WELL, IF YOU AREN'T A SIGHT FOR SORE EYES.

01:07:15.988 --> 01:07:18.295
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY...
OUT OF SIGHT, OUT OF MIND.

01:07:18.338 --> 01:07:20.297
THANK YOU, MOTHER.
WE'LL BE FINE.

01:07:20.340 --> 01:07:22.342
YOU CAN GO NOW.

01:07:25.563 --> 01:07:27.956
BOBBY, YOU KNOW,
JOEL'S GONNA FIND OUT

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:29.958
ABOUT YOU AND LAINIE
MONDAY MORNING AT SCHOOL.

01:07:30.002 --> 01:07:33.136
HEY, I TRIED TO WARN YOU.
DID YOU LISTEN? NO.

01:07:33.179 --> 01:07:36.356
YEAH, WELL, HOPEFULLY I
WON'T BE IN SCHOOL MONDAY.

01:07:36.400 --> 01:07:39.403
THAT'S A REAL GOOD IDEA, PAL...
REAL GOOD.

01:07:39.446 --> 01:07:41.187
BOBBY, LET ME ASK YOU
A QUESTION.

01:07:41.231 --> 01:07:43.363
DO YOU REALLY, HONESTLY
KNOW WHAT YOU'RE DOING?

01:07:43.407 --> 01:07:45.713
- NO, NO, NO, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
- [ coughing ]

01:07:45.757 --> 01:07:48.107
FORGET I ASKED.
YOU OBVIOUSLY DON'T.

01:07:48.151 --> 01:07:50.675
YOU KEEP PROVING IT
TO ME.

01:07:50.718 --> 01:07:52.677
LISTEN, DINGER,

01:07:52.720 --> 01:07:55.027
I JUST WANT TO SAY
THAT, YOU KNOW,

01:07:55.071 --> 01:07:57.464
I APPRECIATE US BEING
FRIENDS AND EVERYTHING

01:07:57.508 --> 01:08:00.641
AND YOU HELPING ME
THROUGH THIS.

01:08:00.685 --> 01:08:02.469
I GOT IT.
YOU WANT MONEY.

01:08:02.513 --> 01:08:04.254
THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT,
RIGHT... MONEY?

01:08:04.297 --> 01:08:06.256
NO, NO, NOT AT ALL.

01:08:06.299 --> 01:08:08.823
I JUST WANTED
TO LET YOU KNOW

01:08:08.867 --> 01:08:11.261
I APPRECIATE
YOU BEING MY FRIEND.

01:08:11.304 --> 01:08:12.697
BOBBY.

01:08:12.740 --> 01:08:15.700
YEAH?

01:08:15.743 --> 01:08:19.182
DUDE, ARE YOU TURNING FAG ON ME OR WHAT?
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

01:08:19.225 --> 01:08:21.184
WHAT'S WRONG?

01:08:21.227 --> 01:08:23.185
WHERE WERE YOU?

01:08:23.229 --> 01:08:25.796
AT THE GYM.
I'M WORKING ON SOMETHING.

01:08:25.840 --> 01:08:28.147
OH, YEAH?
I WENT THERE LOOKING FOR YOU, LAINIE.

01:08:28.191 --> 01:08:30.932
OH.

01:08:30.975 --> 01:08:34.109
LOOK, LISTEN, I'M TRYING TO BE
COOL ABOUT THIS, ALL RIGHT?

01:08:34.153 --> 01:08:36.938
BUT YOU'RE DOING SOMETHING
BEHIND MY BACK.

01:08:36.982 --> 01:08:39.550
DO I HAVE TO FIND OUT
FOR MYSELF?

01:08:39.593 --> 01:08:42.247
I DON'T KNOW. I DON'T
WANT TO DO THIS TO YOU.

01:08:42.292 --> 01:08:44.990
IT'S JUST...
I JUST DON'T KNOW ABOUT ANYTHING ANYMORE.

01:08:45.033 --> 01:08:47.122
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO...
WAIT ON YOU TO FIGURE THINGS OUT?

01:08:47.166 --> 01:08:49.125
I MEAN,
GOD DAMN IT, LAINIE!

01:08:49.167 --> 01:08:51.692
I'M SORRY, JOEL.

01:08:51.736 --> 01:08:54.086
I JUST CAN'T TALK
ABOUT THIS RIGHT NOW.

01:08:54.130 --> 01:08:56.871
LOOK, I'LL MEET YOU
TOMORROW AT THE DANCE, OKAY?

01:08:56.915 --> 01:08:58.917
I'LL BE READY THEN.
I PROMISE.

01:08:58.960 --> 01:09:02.050
GREAT. GREAT. WELL, LISTEN, YOU'D
BETTER STRAIGHTEN YOUR ACT OUT BY THEN,

01:09:02.094 --> 01:09:04.618
'CAUSE I'M NOT GONNA WAIT
AROUND FOR YOU TO GROW UP.

01:09:06.577 --> 01:09:08.752
NOW COME HERE.

01:09:15.673 --> 01:09:17.196
ALL RIGHT, GOOD.

01:09:17.240 --> 01:09:20.286
SO WHAT DID YOU TELL
GARSON AND SHEILA?

01:09:20.330 --> 01:09:23.158
WELL, I TOLD THEM I'D SIGNED
UP AT THE BRIDGE CLUB

01:09:23.202 --> 01:09:24.986
TO BE A SURROGATE
GRANDFATHER

01:09:25.029 --> 01:09:26.814
FOR KIDS THAT
DON'T HAVE ONE...

01:09:26.858 --> 01:09:28.816
YOU KNOW, BIG GRANDPAS
OF AMERICA.

01:09:28.859 --> 01:09:31.428
[ laughs ]

01:09:31.470 --> 01:09:33.778
DO YOU FIND IT
AMUSING?

01:09:33.821 --> 01:09:36.171
OH, I THINK IT'S
GREAT, ACTUALLY.

01:09:36.215 --> 01:09:39.566
WELL, THERE'S NOTHING FUNNY
ABOUT THIS, COLEMAN.

01:09:39.609 --> 01:09:41.394
OH, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

01:09:41.438 --> 01:09:44.005
AS A MATTER OF FACT, THERE'S A
LOT OF FUNNY THINGS ABOUT THIS.

01:09:44.049 --> 01:09:47.139
FOR INSTANCE, I HAPPEN TO BE DATING
MY BEST FRIEND'S GIRLFRIEND;

01:09:47.183 --> 01:09:49.488
I'VE GOTTEN IN TWO
FIGHTS IN TWO DAYS.

01:09:49.533 --> 01:09:52.057
I MEAN, LOOK AT MY FACE.
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

01:09:52.100 --> 01:09:55.191
JUST LOOKS LIKE A BAD
CASE OF ACNE TO ME.

01:09:55.234 --> 01:09:57.497
THAT WAS A GOOD ONE,
IKE.

01:09:57.541 --> 01:09:59.499
I'M IMPRESSED.
I'M VERY IMPRESSED.

01:09:59.543 --> 01:10:01.762
BUT SERIOUSLY,
NOW I GOTTA GO HOME

01:10:01.806 --> 01:10:03.938
AND GET SHIT FROM MY PARENTS
FOR BEING LATE AGAIN.

01:10:03.982 --> 01:10:05.940
AND THE TEACHING
AT THAT SCHOOL

01:10:05.984 --> 01:10:09.074
HAS DECLINED FASTER THAN
THE WESTERN CIVILIZATION.

01:10:09.117 --> 01:10:12.512
IT'S RIDICULOUS. THEY DON'T TEACH YOU
ANYTHING YOU NEED TO KNOW ANYMORE.

01:10:12.556 --> 01:10:15.559
THEY TEACH YOU NOTHING
THAT'S SPIRITUAL OR UPLIFTING.

01:10:15.602 --> 01:10:18.431
NOT AS EASY
AS YOU THOUGHT, HUH?

01:10:18.475 --> 01:10:20.433
HEY, WILL YOU DO ME
A FAVOR, PAL?

01:10:20.477 --> 01:10:23.175
CUT ME SOME SLACK.

01:10:23.219 --> 01:10:25.699
- CUT YOU SOME SLACK?
- YEAH.

01:10:25.743 --> 01:10:28.572
- LAINIE.
- NOT NOW, MOTHER.

01:10:28.615 --> 01:10:30.356
DON'T YOU THINK
YOU SHOULD TELL HIM?

01:10:30.400 --> 01:10:32.924
TELL HIM WHAT?
THERE'S NOTHING TO TELL.

01:10:32.967 --> 01:10:34.969
I THINK YOU'RE MAKING
A BIG MISTAKE.

01:10:36.493 --> 01:10:38.973
WHAT'S HAPPENING
TO YOU, LAINIE?

01:10:39.017 --> 01:10:42.412
AND DON'T WORRY ABOUT THE CAR.
I'LL GET THAT FIXED.

01:10:42.455 --> 01:10:43.978
COLEMAN.

01:10:44.022 --> 01:10:45.676
YEAH?

01:10:45.719 --> 01:10:48.940
HAVE YOU FIGURED OUT HOW
YOU'RE GONNA GET BACK YET?

01:10:48.983 --> 01:10:51.595
[ sighs ]

01:10:53.031 --> 01:10:56.817
I GUESS I'M GONNA HAVE TO
REPEAT THE EXPERIMENT.

01:10:56.861 --> 01:11:00.343
IT'LL WORK.
DON'T WORRY.

01:11:00.386 --> 01:11:03.302
THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING.

01:11:03.346 --> 01:11:05.652
WHAT ARE
BIG GRANDPAS FOR?

01:11:08.742 --> 01:11:11.267
[ engine starts ]

01:11:19.927 --> 01:11:23.409
I MEAN, WHAT THE HELL
DOES HE STUDY?

01:11:23.453 --> 01:11:25.716
YOU GOTTA...
YOU GOTTA TELL HIM

01:11:25.759 --> 01:11:28.327
THAT IF HE FLUNKS THAT S.A.T.
TEST, THAT WE'RE GONNA BE...

01:11:28.371 --> 01:11:30.764
GUS, YOU CAN'T FLUNK
THAT KIND OF A TEST.

01:11:30.808 --> 01:11:32.766
HE'LL FIND A WAY. COME ON.

01:11:32.810 --> 01:11:34.507
I MEAN, IT'S ALWAYS SOMETHING.

01:11:34.551 --> 01:11:36.988
IF HE DOESN'T
GET INTO COLLEGE...

01:11:38.294 --> 01:11:40.600
- LOOK AT THIS.
- OH.

01:11:40.644 --> 01:11:43.124
CAN YOU IMAGINE
WHAT HE'S DONE NOW?

01:11:43.168 --> 01:11:45.910
ASK HIM IF THE POLICE
ARE VERY FAR BEHIND HIM.

01:11:45.953 --> 01:11:48.434
IT'S THOSE NO-GOOD
FRIENDS OF HIS.

01:11:48.478 --> 01:11:50.784
THE POLICE ARE NOT BEHIND ME.
AND IT'S NOT MY FRIENDS, OKAY?

01:11:50.828 --> 01:11:52.569
MY FRIENDS WOULDN'T
BEAT ME UP LIKE THIS.

01:11:52.612 --> 01:11:54.919
ASK HIM IF I'M GONNA
GET SUED.

01:11:54.962 --> 01:11:56.747
CHECK OUT IF HE'S GOT
ANY TEETH LEFT.

01:11:56.790 --> 01:11:58.531
I CAN'T AFFORD
THE DENTAL BILLS.

01:11:58.575 --> 01:12:01.795
YOU KNOW, IT'S NO WONDER
I'M SO SCREWED UP.

01:12:01.839 --> 01:12:03.710
I MEAN, LOOK AT YOU GUYS.
YOU DON'T EVEN TALK TO ME.

01:12:03.754 --> 01:12:05.712
I'M YOUR SON, REMEMBER?

01:12:05.756 --> 01:12:08.149
WHY DON'T YOU EVER GIVE ME
THE BENEFIT OF A DOUBT?

01:12:08.193 --> 01:12:09.977
YOU DON'T EVEN ASK ME
IF ANYTHING'S WRONG.

01:12:10.021 --> 01:12:11.936
YOU DON'T EVEN
ASK ME IF I'M HURT.

01:12:11.979 --> 01:12:14.417
I MEAN, WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

01:12:14.460 --> 01:12:16.680
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT IT'S LIKE

01:12:16.723 --> 01:12:18.508
TO BE A KID
IN TODAY'S SOCIETY.

01:12:18.551 --> 01:12:20.423
I'M TRYING MY HARDEST.

01:12:24.252 --> 01:12:26.951
I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY I SCREAMED.

01:12:26.994 --> 01:12:29.432
IT'S JUST
REALLY UPSETTING.

01:12:29.475 --> 01:12:32.348
I TRY TO DO
EVERYTHING I CAN.

01:12:32.391 --> 01:12:34.741
AND I'M STUDYING HARD.

01:12:34.785 --> 01:12:38.223
AND I'M GONNA DO GOOD ON MY S.A.T.s
ON SATURDAY. I'M GOING TO.

01:12:38.266 --> 01:12:40.965
YEAH, SURE.

01:12:41.008 --> 01:12:43.315
I MEAN, I'M WORKING
REALLY HARD.

01:12:43.359 --> 01:12:45.796
I JUST NEED YOU
TO HELP ME.

01:12:45.839 --> 01:12:47.972
I CANNOT DO THIS
WITHOUT YOU.

01:12:48.015 --> 01:12:50.017
OKAY.

01:12:51.584 --> 01:12:52.716
OKAY.

01:12:52.759 --> 01:12:56.023
GOOD NIGHT.
GOOD NIGHT, GUS

01:12:56.067 --> 01:12:58.374
AND KIT.

01:12:58.417 --> 01:13:01.246
GOOD NIGHT.

01:13:01.289 --> 01:13:03.640
GOOD NIGHT, HONEY.

01:13:07.513 --> 01:13:10.081
WHEN DID HE START
CALLING US GUS AND KIT?

01:13:30.318 --> 01:13:33.496
♪ I NEVER WANT TO
SEE YOU LONELY ♪

01:13:33.539 --> 01:13:35.106
♪ AGAIN ♪

01:13:35.149 --> 01:13:37.108
♪ 'CAUSE I KNOW ♪

01:13:37.151 --> 01:13:41.286
♪ LIFE IS TO LOVE FOREVER ♪

01:13:43.375 --> 01:13:46.030
♪ WHEN I SEE YOU STANDING ♪

01:13:46.073 --> 01:13:48.467
♪ ALL ALONE IN THE WIND ♪

01:13:48.511 --> 01:13:52.297
♪ I BELIEVE WE CAN FLY ♪

01:13:52.340 --> 01:13:55.126
♪ SO HIGH ABOVE ♪

01:13:55.169 --> 01:13:57.128
♪ YOU KNOW I ALWAYS ASK ♪

01:13:57.171 --> 01:14:01.828
♪ FOR MORE EMOTION ♪

01:14:01.872 --> 01:14:05.528
♪ OH ♪

01:14:05.571 --> 01:14:09.662
♪ WHENEVER THERE'S A
NIGHT YOU NEED LOVE ♪

01:14:09.706 --> 01:14:13.057
♪ CALL MY NAME AND
TO YOU I'LL RUN ♪

01:14:13.100 --> 01:14:16.321
♪ FEELING IN A HEART,
WILD AND YOUNG ♪

01:14:16.364 --> 01:14:19.629
♪ PASSION MAKING TWO INTO ONE ♪

01:14:19.672 --> 01:14:22.675
♪ WHENEVER THERE'S A
NIGHT YOU NEED LOVE ♪

01:14:22.719 --> 01:14:24.677
♪ I WILL MAKE IT SHINE ♪

01:14:24.721 --> 01:14:29.116
♪ LIKE THE SUN ♪

01:14:30.509 --> 01:14:33.469
♪ SOMETIMES I REACH
TO TOUCH YOU ♪

01:14:33.512 --> 01:14:35.166
♪ AGAIN ♪

01:14:35.209 --> 01:14:38.604
♪ AND I KNOW THE
SPIRIT WILL LIVE ♪

01:14:38.648 --> 01:14:41.128
♪ FOREVER ♪

01:14:43.479 --> 01:14:45.045
♪ NOW I WANT YOU ♪

01:14:45.089 --> 01:14:48.440
♪ AS MY LOVER AND MY FRIEND ♪

01:14:48.484 --> 01:14:50.442
♪ 'CAUSE I KNOW... ♪

01:14:50.486 --> 01:14:53.053
- BOBBY?
- YOU RANG?

01:14:54.359 --> 01:14:57.797
YOU KNOW, YOU SHOULD
TAKE BETTER CARE OF ME.

01:15:01.584 --> 01:15:03.542
NOBODY'S HERE.

01:15:03.586 --> 01:15:05.544
NO, THEY'RE ALL PACKED UP
AND READY TO GO.

01:15:05.588 --> 01:15:08.112
YOU'VE GOT TO SHOW ME
HOW TO MAKE THE SWITCH.

01:15:08.155 --> 01:15:09.417
NO WAY.

01:15:09.461 --> 01:15:11.419
BUT WE'RE GETTING THINGS
STRAIGHTENED OUT.

01:15:11.463 --> 01:15:13.247
I'M GONNA GET YOU
INTO COLLEGE.

01:15:13.291 --> 01:15:14.814
YOU'LL HAVE A FUTURE.

01:15:14.858 --> 01:15:17.643
AND LAINIE'S A TERRIFIC GIRL.
EVERYTHING'S GOING FINE.

01:15:17.687 --> 01:15:20.341
YOU DON'T THINK THAT I SEE THE
WAY YOU'VE SCREWED THINGS UP?

01:15:20.385 --> 01:15:22.343
YOU SCREWED MY LIFE UP
WORSE THAN I DID.

01:15:22.387 --> 01:15:24.824
YOU JUST DO NOT UNDERSTAND WHAT IT'S LIKE

01:15:24.868 --> 01:15:27.610
TO GO THROUGH LIFE IN TODAY'S WORLD WITH A KID'S EMOTION.

01:15:27.653 --> 01:15:29.525
YEAN, YOU'RE RIGHT.
MAYBE I DON'T.

01:15:29.568 --> 01:15:31.962
I MAKE A LOUSY KID.

01:15:32.005 --> 01:15:35.008
I'M TOO CAUTIOUS.
I LACK SPONTANEITY.

01:15:35.052 --> 01:15:38.621
I WOULDN'T DARE TO HANG MY ASS OUT OF
A WINDOW AND MOON A LOT OF STRANGERS

01:15:38.664 --> 01:15:41.319
OR THROW UP
IN THE BACKSEAT OF A CAR.

01:15:41.362 --> 01:15:43.495
IT'S YOUR LIFE.
YOU HAVE TO LIVE IT.

01:15:43.539 --> 01:15:46.237
NOT ANYMORE,
THANKS TO YOU.

01:15:46.280 --> 01:15:48.805
WHERE'S GENA?

01:15:48.848 --> 01:15:51.677
I SAW HER IN THE HOUSE
A FEW MINUTES AGO,

01:15:51.721 --> 01:15:54.027
TAKING CARE OF SOME LAST-MINUTE THINGS.

01:15:59.076 --> 01:16:02.035
GENA'S TRYING TO TELL
LAINIE WHAT HAPPENED.

01:16:02.079 --> 01:16:03.559
I STILL HAVE
A CHANCE.

01:16:03.602 --> 01:16:05.082
NOT WITHOUT ME,
YOU DON'T.

01:16:05.125 --> 01:16:06.605
AND YOU WON'T
EVEN HELP ME?

01:16:06.649 --> 01:16:08.955
I CAN'T.
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

01:16:08.999 --> 01:16:12.045
IT'S NOT GONNA BE IN MY
BEST INTERESTS TO HELP YOU.

01:16:12.089 --> 01:16:14.526
I CAN DO ONE THING... I CAN GIVE YOU A HINT.

01:16:14.570 --> 01:16:17.660
OKAY, FIRST OF ALL,
IT HAS NOTHING TO DO

01:16:17.703 --> 01:16:20.097
WITH STATES AND SYSTEMS
AND ALL THAT SHIT.

01:16:20.140 --> 01:16:22.316
SECONDLY, IT HAS NOTHING
TO DO WITH PHYSICS.

01:16:22.360 --> 01:16:24.492
AND ALSO, IF YOU WEREN'T
SO DAMNED SMART,

01:16:24.536 --> 01:16:27.017
YOU WOULD HAVE FIGURED THIS
WHOLE THING OUT TWO DREAMS AGO.

01:16:27.060 --> 01:16:29.585
THAT'S ALL I CAN SAY, POPS.

01:16:31.587 --> 01:16:32.849
HEY,

01:16:32.892 --> 01:16:35.416
AREN'T YOU GONNA TELL ME
NOT TO CALL YOU "POPS"?

01:16:37.897 --> 01:16:42.032
WHEW. WOW.

01:16:42.075 --> 01:16:43.773
I GUESS THAT'S IT.

01:16:46.253 --> 01:16:49.256
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.
I'M HISTORY.

01:16:51.215 --> 01:16:53.347
KEEP DREAMING.

01:17:21.811 --> 01:17:24.161
[ Bobby's voice ]
LAST DAY, POPS. GOOD LUCK.

01:17:24.204 --> 01:17:25.684
HEH!

01:17:25.728 --> 01:17:28.905
ALL RIGHT, PENCILS UP.

01:17:28.948 --> 01:17:30.907
GOOD MORNING.

01:17:30.950 --> 01:17:33.605
WELCOME TO THE SCHOLASTIC
APTITUDE TEST.

01:17:33.649 --> 01:17:35.912
REMEMBER DURING THE TEST

01:17:35.955 --> 01:17:37.914
TO REMAIN IN YOUR SEATS

01:17:37.957 --> 01:17:41.613
AND LET THERE BE
ABSOLUTELY NO TALKING.

01:17:41.657 --> 01:17:44.007
THIS TEST IS TO DETERMINE
YOUR ABILITY

01:17:44.050 --> 01:17:46.400
TO GET INTO COLLEGE.

01:17:46.444 --> 01:17:49.839
SOME OF YOU
I DON'T THINK WILL MAKE IT.

01:17:49.882 --> 01:17:53.277
IT IS NOW 10:07.

01:17:53.320 --> 01:17:56.715
YOU HAVE UNTIL 1:07.

01:17:56.759 --> 01:17:58.717
AND YOU MAY OPEN
YOUR TEST BOOKS...

01:17:58.761 --> 01:18:00.850
NOW!

01:18:08.205 --> 01:18:10.250
[ growling ]

01:18:49.768 --> 01:18:51.509
[ mouths ]

01:18:56.340 --> 01:18:58.690
HEY, MR. PATTISON,
LISTEN.

01:18:58.734 --> 01:19:01.345
SOME OF THE QUESTIONS IN THE
TEST WERE WRONG ON THEIR FACE,

01:19:01.388 --> 01:19:03.173
SO I WENT AHEAD
AND CORRECTED THEM.

01:19:03.216 --> 01:19:05.653
THEY'RE IN THE TEXTBOOK,
SO TAKE A LOOK, OKAY?

01:19:05.697 --> 01:19:07.699
THANKS.

01:19:22.583 --> 01:19:25.238
HEY, I ADMIT I DREAMED ABOUT
THE OLD COUPLE LAST NIGHT.

01:19:25.282 --> 01:19:26.805
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED
TO DO ABOUT IT?

01:19:26.849 --> 01:19:29.286
I MEAN, THIS DOESN'T MEAN
YOU'RE RIGHT, YOU KNOW.

01:19:29.329 --> 01:19:31.723
AND HOW DO YOU
EXPLAIN THE DREAM?

01:19:31.767 --> 01:19:35.727
A STRONG POWER OF SUGGESTION
PLANTED IN A TENDER YOUNG MIND

01:19:35.771 --> 01:19:39.078
BY A CLEVER YOUNG MAN WITH A NOVEL
APPROACH TO STEALING HIS FRIEND'S GIRL.

01:19:39.122 --> 01:19:43.387
YEAH, WELL, THAT'S NOT AT ALL WHAT
I'M DOING, BUT IS IT WORKING?

01:19:43.430 --> 01:19:45.737
IN A WAY.
THIS IS A BIZARRE COURTSHIP.

01:19:45.781 --> 01:19:47.347
YES, IT'S VERY
STRANGE.

01:19:47.391 --> 01:19:49.872
BUT LET'S PUT ALL THAT ASIDE.
LET'S GET BACK TO THE ARGUING.

01:19:49.915 --> 01:19:51.874
WHAT AM I GONNA DO
WITH YOU?

01:19:51.917 --> 01:19:53.440
I WOULD SAY
WE SHOULD GET MARRIED,

01:19:53.484 --> 01:19:55.486
BUT WE CAN'T,
'CAUSE WE ALREADY ARE.

01:19:55.529 --> 01:19:58.141
OKAY, I'M NOT SAYING
I BELIEVE YOU,

01:19:58.184 --> 01:19:59.969
BUT COME HERE
AND KISS ME.

01:20:01.797 --> 01:20:03.102
BOO.

01:20:03.146 --> 01:20:05.583
SCARED YOU, HUH?

01:20:05.626 --> 01:20:07.585
LOOK, MINE IS NOT
THE QUESTION;

01:20:07.628 --> 01:20:09.935
MINE IS ONLY
A WARNING FOR YOU TWO.

01:20:09.979 --> 01:20:12.633
JOEL IS VERY
CLOSE BEHIND.

01:20:12.677 --> 01:20:14.679
[ giggles ]

01:20:15.941 --> 01:20:18.596
LOOK, IN THAT DREAM,
SHE WAS REALLY REAL.

01:20:18.639 --> 01:20:20.990
SHE SAID I COULDN'T FALL ASLEEP
OR WE'D LOSE THEM FOREVER...

01:20:21.033 --> 01:20:22.992
LIKE OZ
OR SOMETHING.

01:20:23.035 --> 01:20:25.995
- WHAT ELSE DID SHE SAY?
- SHE SAID THAT SHE REALLY LOVES YOU.

01:20:26.038 --> 01:20:29.999
LAINIE, THAT WAS
A SECRET. GOD.

01:20:30.042 --> 01:20:32.001
EXCUSE ME.
SHELLEY.

01:20:32.044 --> 01:20:34.699
- WOMEN ARE NUTS.
- YOU'RE TELLING ME.

01:20:34.742 --> 01:20:37.093
HEY, ASSHOLE.

01:20:37.136 --> 01:20:39.095
- HEY, HEY.
- JOEL, JOEL.

01:20:39.138 --> 01:20:41.358
THE POOR GUY IS MY BUDDY.
NOW IT'S BETWEEN ME AND YOU.

01:20:41.401 --> 01:20:43.055
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, JOEL?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:20:43.099 --> 01:20:44.796
STOP IT, JOEL.
THAT'S ENOUGH.

01:20:44.840 --> 01:20:46.319
HEY, I'M DOING THIS
FOR YOU, ALL RIGHT?

01:20:46.363 --> 01:20:47.843
I DON'T NEED IT,
ALL RIGHT?

01:20:47.886 --> 01:20:49.409
I DIDN'T NEED IT
LAST NIGHT.

01:20:49.453 --> 01:20:51.237
DINGER DIDN'T NEED IT THE OTHER
DAY ON THE FOOTBALL FIELD.

01:20:51.281 --> 01:20:54.023
AND NONE OF US NEED IT NOW.
THAT'S ENOUGH OF THIS SHIT.

01:20:54.066 --> 01:20:56.547
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT, I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.

01:20:56.590 --> 01:20:58.549
- [ door opens ]
- HEY, ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

01:20:58.592 --> 01:21:00.290
- HEY, YOU.
- THAT'S FOR ME.

01:21:00.333 --> 01:21:02.988
- YOU, OUT OF HERE. YOU, INSIDE.
- I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

01:21:03.032 --> 01:21:04.990
- YOU, COME WITH ME.
- I CAN'T. COME ON.

01:21:05.034 --> 01:21:06.209
- LET'S GO.
- I CAN'T GO.

01:21:06.252 --> 01:21:07.775
Dinger:
WHY ME? WHY ALWAYS ME?

01:21:11.867 --> 01:21:13.825
WOW, I ALWAYS THOUGHT
"S.A.T." MEANT

01:21:13.869 --> 01:21:16.784
"SATURDAY AFTERNOON TEST."
WHAT IS UP?

01:21:40.634 --> 01:21:42.332
OH, IT'S YOU.

01:21:42.375 --> 01:21:44.203
YEAH, IS LAINIE HOME?

01:21:45.596 --> 01:21:47.032
NOPE.

01:21:47.076 --> 01:21:48.816
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE SHE'S AT?

01:21:48.860 --> 01:21:50.340
I THOUGHT MAYBE
SHE WAS WITH YOU,

01:21:50.383 --> 01:21:52.516
SO I GUESS THINGS
COULD BE WORSE.

01:21:52.559 --> 01:21:54.344
YOU DON'T CARE MUCH
FOR ME, DO YOU?

01:21:54.387 --> 01:21:56.346
WHAT'S NOT TO LIKE?

01:21:56.389 --> 01:21:58.565
I'LL BE SURE TO TELL HER
YOU CAME BY.

01:22:06.573 --> 01:22:08.532
LATELY WHERE YOU FIND
THAT KELLER BOY,

01:22:08.575 --> 01:22:10.969
YOU FIND MY DAUGHTER.

01:22:11.013 --> 01:22:13.189
NOW WE LIKE YOU
A LOT, JOEL.

01:22:13.232 --> 01:22:15.234
WE'D LIKE TO SEE YOU
IN THE FAMILY.

01:22:16.322 --> 01:22:20.239
♪ WHERE IS SHE? WHERE IS SHE? ♪

01:22:20.283 --> 01:22:22.676
♪ I KEEP WAITING ♪

01:22:22.720 --> 01:22:25.766
♪ FOR A CALL ♪

01:22:27.116 --> 01:22:30.293
♪ WHERE IS SHE? WHERE IS SHE? ♪

01:22:30.336 --> 01:22:31.816
[ door opens ]

01:22:31.859 --> 01:22:34.993
FOR SOME REASON,
I'M JEALOUS OF HER.

01:22:35.037 --> 01:22:38.736
I'M NOT SURE I BELIEVE
I AM WHO YOU SAY I AM

01:22:38.779 --> 01:22:42.087
OR IF I JUST WANT YOU
TO WANT ME MORE.

01:22:58.625 --> 01:23:01.193
I THINK WHAT SHE WAS
TRYING TO TELL US

01:23:01.237 --> 01:23:03.804
IS THAT WE CAN'T
FALL ASLEEP TONIGHT

01:23:03.848 --> 01:23:06.198
OR WE COULD
LOSE THEM FOREVER.

01:23:06.242 --> 01:23:08.244
BOBBY, I'M AS ANXIOUS TO
MATURE AS THE NEXT GIRL,

01:23:08.287 --> 01:23:11.073
BUT I'M NOT LOOKING TO
RUSH IT QUITE THAT MUCH.

01:23:11.116 --> 01:23:14.250
I DON'T THINK
YOU GET IT.

01:23:14.293 --> 01:23:16.252
THERE'S REALLY
NO RISK.

01:23:16.295 --> 01:23:19.255
BOBBY AND LAINIE
WILL ALWAYS EXIST.

01:23:19.298 --> 01:23:21.257
WILL I STILL
LIKE YOU...

01:23:21.300 --> 01:23:24.782
I MEAN, AFTER,
YOU KNOW...?

01:23:24.825 --> 01:23:27.263
I HOPE SO.

01:23:27.306 --> 01:23:29.265
I DON'T KNOW.

01:23:29.308 --> 01:23:31.702
I DON'T WANT
TO LOSE YOU, BOBBY.

01:23:31.745 --> 01:23:35.967
I DON'T WANT
TO LOSE ME EITHER.

01:23:36.011 --> 01:23:38.970
COME ON, YOU ALWAYS SAID
YOU LIKED ADVENTURE.

01:23:39.014 --> 01:23:41.059
YEAH, I KNOW,

01:23:41.103 --> 01:23:43.888
BUT I'M NOT SO SURE
ABOUT THIS.

01:23:43.931 --> 01:23:45.455
PLEASE.

01:23:45.498 --> 01:23:49.024
I NEED YOU TO DO THIS
WITH ME.

01:23:49.067 --> 01:23:52.114
OKAY.

01:23:52.157 --> 01:23:54.246
I'LL DO THIS WITH YOU
IF YOU PROMISE ME

01:23:54.290 --> 01:23:55.987
THAT AFTER THIS YOU'LL
NEVER BRING IT UP AGAIN.

01:23:56.031 --> 01:23:57.945
OKAY, I PROMISE.

01:23:57.989 --> 01:24:00.209
SWEETHEART,

01:24:00.252 --> 01:24:02.776
- JOEL WAS HERE LOOKING FOR YOU.
- GREAT.

01:24:02.820 --> 01:24:05.214
BOBBY, PLEASE, LET'S NOT
CAUSE A SCENE TONIGHT, OKAY?

01:24:05.257 --> 01:24:07.303
I'LL GO WITH JOEL
AND YOU GO WITH SHELLEY.

01:24:07.346 --> 01:24:09.435
WE CAN DEAL WITH
ALL THAT LATER.

01:24:09.479 --> 01:24:13.874
BUT I NEED TO BE
ALONE WITH YOU TONIGHT.

01:24:13.918 --> 01:24:15.659
I TOLD HIM I DIDN'T KNOW
WHERE YOU WERE.

01:24:15.702 --> 01:24:17.400
I GOTTA GO.

01:24:17.443 --> 01:24:19.793
LOOK, WE'LL BE ALONE
AFTER THE DANCE, OKAY?

01:24:19.837 --> 01:24:21.839
OKAY.

01:24:40.379 --> 01:24:42.686
BOBBY.

01:24:42.729 --> 01:24:44.818
YO.

01:24:44.862 --> 01:24:46.864
TELL HIM HOW NICE
HE LOOKS.

01:24:46.907 --> 01:24:48.866
NO, YOU TELL HIM
HOW NICE HE LOOKS.

01:24:48.909 --> 01:24:50.694
NO, TELL HIM
WHAT YOU TOLD ME.

01:24:50.737 --> 01:24:52.957
OH.

01:24:57.135 --> 01:24:59.529
UM, SON,

01:24:59.572 --> 01:25:02.053
BOBBY,

01:25:02.097 --> 01:25:04.403
I JUST WANT
TO TELL YOU

01:25:04.447 --> 01:25:06.405
THAT WHAT YOU SAID
LAST NIGHT

01:25:06.449 --> 01:25:08.407
MADE US DO
A LOT OF THINKING.

01:25:08.451 --> 01:25:10.409
YOU WERE RIGHT.

01:25:10.453 --> 01:25:12.759
WE DON'T LISTEN
TO YOUR PROBLEMS.

01:25:12.803 --> 01:25:14.283
THANK YOU.

01:25:14.326 --> 01:25:17.242
TELL HIM WE'LL TRY
TO DO A BETTER JOB.

01:25:18.939 --> 01:25:22.595
UM, YOU HEARD
WHAT YOUR FATHER SAID.

01:25:22.639 --> 01:25:26.817
YEAH, I HEARD HIM.
LISTEN, MOM,

01:25:26.860 --> 01:25:28.819
COULD YOU TELL DAD

01:25:28.862 --> 01:25:32.388
THAT I LOVE HIM
AND I LOVE YOU TOO

01:25:32.431 --> 01:25:34.955
AND I'M GONNA
MISS YOU BOTH

01:25:34.999 --> 01:25:37.741
IN A WEIRD SORT OF WAY?
I MEAN THAT.

01:25:37.784 --> 01:25:40.004
I GOT A DANCE TO GO TO.

01:25:40.047 --> 01:25:42.049
I GOTTA GO.

01:25:45.923 --> 01:25:47.403
WHEN HE COMES BACK,

01:25:47.446 --> 01:25:49.448
WILL YOU ASK HIM
WHAT HE MEANT BY THAT?

01:25:52.495 --> 01:25:54.540
THIS IS TERRIFIC.

01:25:54.584 --> 01:25:56.542
I KNOW YOU LIKE IT
CRUNCHY.

01:25:56.586 --> 01:25:58.153
[ chuckles ]

01:25:58.196 --> 01:26:00.459
[ dance music playing ]

01:26:19.913 --> 01:26:22.438
HEY, WHAT,
ARE YOU NUTS, MAN?

01:26:22.481 --> 01:26:24.918
- SHUT UP.
- JOEL.

01:26:31.838 --> 01:26:33.797
HEY, BOBBY.

01:26:33.840 --> 01:26:35.799
HEY, KELLER, MAN,
WHERE'S LAINIE?

01:26:35.842 --> 01:26:37.714
LOOKING FOR YOU.

01:26:37.757 --> 01:26:40.020
I THINK YOU SHOULD TALK TO ME.
COME HERE, PLEASE.

01:26:40.064 --> 01:26:41.413
WHAT WAS THAT
ALL ABOUT?

01:26:41.457 --> 01:26:43.459
I DON'T KNOW, BUT HE'S
GETTING REALLY TRASHED.

01:26:43.502 --> 01:26:45.156
THEY'LL WORK IT OUT.

01:26:45.200 --> 01:26:47.202
LOOK, IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.
EVER SINCE THE ACCIDENT...

01:26:47.245 --> 01:26:49.900
HEY, THERE ARE NO ACCIDENTS.
IS THAT WHY YOU'VE BEEN SO FRIGID, HUH?

01:26:49.943 --> 01:26:52.642
NOW YOU OWE ME.

01:26:52.685 --> 01:26:54.426
- STOP IT, JOEL.
- HEY, FUCK YOU.

01:26:54.470 --> 01:26:56.907
- WHY CAN'T I EVEN SAY IT, HUH?
- YOU KNOW, JOEL, JUST HIT ME.

01:26:56.950 --> 01:26:58.735
IT HAS NOTHING TO DO WITH BOBBY.
IT WAS YOU,

01:26:58.778 --> 01:27:00.824
WHAT YOU WANTED.
YOU DON'T GIVE A SHIT ABOUT ME.

01:27:00.867 --> 01:27:02.652
WELL, I DO.
AND I WANT OUT.

01:27:02.695 --> 01:27:04.262
NO GODDAMN WAY.
YOU'RE MINE.

01:27:04.306 --> 01:27:05.655
GET OFF.

01:27:05.698 --> 01:27:08.310
- HEY!
- WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING, MAN?

01:27:08.353 --> 01:27:10.834
- ARE YOU OKAY?
- GET HER OUT OF HERE, GO.

01:27:10.877 --> 01:27:12.836
COME ON, COME ON,
LET'S GO.

01:27:12.879 --> 01:27:14.881
- WATCH OUT!
- Dinger: GO.

01:27:18.798 --> 01:27:20.539
- RELAX, MAN.
- I'M ALL RIGHT. I'M ALL RIGHT.

01:27:20.583 --> 01:27:21.888
SHIT.

01:27:21.932 --> 01:27:24.456
JOEL, JOEL.

01:27:29.418 --> 01:27:31.376
HEY, PRETTY BOY,
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

01:27:31.420 --> 01:27:33.422
FAGGOT.

01:27:35.380 --> 01:27:37.687
COME ON, LAINIE.

01:27:37.730 --> 01:27:39.950
[ engine starts ]

01:27:41.038 --> 01:27:43.345
[ tires screech ]

01:27:43.388 --> 01:27:45.347
OH, GEE, I'M SORRY
ABOUT THAT, JOEL.

01:27:45.390 --> 01:27:47.871
YOU KNOW, I SHOULDN'T HAVE
TOLD YOU I SAW THEM TOGETHER.

01:27:47.914 --> 01:27:49.351
I GUESS I'M NOT
A VERY GOOD FRIEND.

01:27:49.394 --> 01:27:51.266
HEY, FAGGOT, YOU'RE DEAD.
YOU'RE GODDAMN DEAD.

01:27:51.309 --> 01:27:53.877
ME AND MY FRIENDS ARE HAVING A
LITTLE PARTY TONIGHT AT THE BRIDGE.

01:27:53.920 --> 01:27:57.489
AND I THINK YOU AND YOU AND ALL YOUR
LITTLE FAGGOT FRIENDS OUGHT TO BE THERE.

01:27:57.533 --> 01:27:59.709
- YOU'RE NOT SO TOUGH NOW, ARE YOU, JOEL?
- FAGGOT.

01:27:59.752 --> 01:28:02.451
LISTEN TO ME.
LISTEN TO ME, ALL RIGHT?

01:28:02.494 --> 01:28:04.583
THEY'RE SHIT.
THEY'RE NOTHING... NOTHING, ALL RIGHT?

01:28:04.627 --> 01:28:06.585
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT.

01:28:06.629 --> 01:28:08.674
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT, MAN.

01:28:10.589 --> 01:28:12.591
OH.

01:28:23.123 --> 01:28:26.431
♪ You can go to extremes ♪

01:28:26.475 --> 01:28:29.347
♪ With impossible schemes ♪

01:28:29.391 --> 01:28:32.437
♪ You can laugh when your dreams ♪

01:28:32.481 --> 01:28:34.874
♪ Fall apart at the seams ♪

01:28:34.918 --> 01:28:38.400
♪ And life gets more exciting ♪

01:28:38.443 --> 01:28:41.359
♪ With each passing day ♪

01:28:41.403 --> 01:28:45.015
♪ And love is either in your heart ♪

01:28:45.058 --> 01:28:47.452
♪ Or on its way ♪

01:28:47.496 --> 01:28:50.586
♪ Don't you know that it's worth ♪

01:28:50.629 --> 01:28:53.545
♪ Every treasure on earth ♪

01:28:53.589 --> 01:28:55.547
♪ To be young ♪

01:28:55.591 --> 01:28:59.334
♪ At heart? ♪

01:28:59.377 --> 01:29:02.293
♪ For as rich as you are ♪

01:29:02.337 --> 01:29:05.557
♪ It's much better by far ♪

01:29:05.601 --> 01:29:08.995
♪ To be young at heart ♪

01:29:11.302 --> 01:29:14.436
♪ And if you should survive ♪

01:29:14.479 --> 01:29:17.613
♪ To 105 ♪

01:29:17.656 --> 01:29:20.398
♪ Look at all you'll derive ♪

01:29:20.442 --> 01:29:23.575
♪ Out of being alive ♪

01:29:23.619 --> 01:29:26.622
♪ And here is the best part ♪

01:29:26.665 --> 01:29:29.799
♪ You had a head start ♪

01:29:29.842 --> 01:29:33.150
♪ If you are among the very ♪

01:29:33.193 --> 01:29:35.587
♪ Young ♪

01:29:35.631 --> 01:29:41.201
♪ At heart ♪

01:29:43.987 --> 01:29:46.772
WOW.

01:29:46.816 --> 01:29:49.166
SHIT'S GETTING WEIRD.

01:29:49.209 --> 01:29:51.168
ME... DINGER,

01:29:51.211 --> 01:29:53.388
THIS UNBELIEVABLY LOOKING GUY,
SITTING OUT HERE,

01:29:53.431 --> 01:29:55.955
FREEZING MY ASS OFF

01:29:55.999 --> 01:29:58.480
IN SOME BUTT-UGLY
RED MUSTANG.

01:29:58.523 --> 01:30:01.439
WELL, WHAT TIME
IS IT?

01:30:01.483 --> 01:30:03.702
I DON'T HAVE A WATCH.
I NEVER HAD A WATCH.

01:30:03.746 --> 01:30:06.488
WHY DID I LOOK
AT MY WRIST?

01:30:06.531 --> 01:30:09.665
HAD A DANCE,
DANCING PERFECTLY

01:30:09.708 --> 01:30:11.797
WITH A HOT CHICK.

01:30:11.841 --> 01:30:13.799
SHE WANTED ME.
I KNOW SHE WANTED ME.

01:30:13.843 --> 01:30:15.497
WELL, EVERY GIRL
WANTS ME.

01:30:15.540 --> 01:30:17.847
I SHOULD BE IN HAWAII
DRINKING A PINA COLADA,

01:30:17.890 --> 01:30:19.849
LOOKING AT SOME
HAWAII CHICK.

01:30:19.892 --> 01:30:21.720
"HELLO, HONEY."

01:30:23.722 --> 01:30:26.290
OH, HERE COMES ASSHOLE.

01:30:29.119 --> 01:30:30.816
WHAT DID YOU GET
IN THERE, MAN?

01:30:30.860 --> 01:30:33.515
GOT A LITTLE MORE
OF THIS

01:30:33.558 --> 01:30:36.300
AND THIS.

01:30:36.343 --> 01:30:39.477
WHAT ARE YOU...
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO WITH THAT, JOEL?

01:30:39.521 --> 01:30:40.957
I'M GONNA DRINK IT.

01:30:41.000 --> 01:30:42.698
I KNOW YOU'RE GONNA
DRINK THAT.

01:30:42.741 --> 01:30:44.613
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO WITH
THE GUN, JOEL... THE GUN?

01:30:44.656 --> 01:30:47.311
HEY, I'M GONNA JOIN THE
PARTY AT THE BRIDGE, MAN,

01:30:47.354 --> 01:30:49.269
AND THE FIRST GUY
THAT PISSES ME OFF

01:30:49.313 --> 01:30:50.923
GETS A LITTLE
SURPRISE.

01:30:50.967 --> 01:30:53.404
JOEL, COME ON, MAN. DON'T YOU THINK
THAT YOU'RE TAKING THIS THING

01:30:53.448 --> 01:30:55.058
- A LITTLE TOO FAR?
- GET OUT OF THE CAR.

01:30:55.101 --> 01:30:56.973
HEY, LOOK, I'M NOT TRYING
TO START SHIT WITH YOU.

01:30:57.016 --> 01:30:59.715
I'M YOUR FRIEND, JOEL.
I DON'T WANT TO SEE YOU GO TO JAIL...

01:30:59.758 --> 01:31:01.499
YOU KNOW, JAIL,
BEHIND BARS.

01:31:01.543 --> 01:31:03.240
HEY, HE HUMILIATED ME,
MAN, ALL RIGHT?

01:31:03.283 --> 01:31:05.503
RIGHT?
I'M NOT GONNA LET THIS SHIT SLIDE.

01:31:05.547 --> 01:31:07.853
LOOK, MAN, I'M NOT GONNA
BE RESPONSIBLE FOR THIS.

01:31:07.897 --> 01:31:09.725
LOOK, IF I HAVE TO,
I'LL STOP YOU.

01:31:09.768 --> 01:31:11.683
HEY, NOBODY'S GONNA STOP
ME AGAIN, ALL RIGHT?

01:31:11.727 --> 01:31:14.033
NOW GET OUT!
OUT!

01:31:14.077 --> 01:31:16.775
- I'M NOT GONNA GET OUT OF THE CAR.
- GET OUT. GET THE HELL OUT.

01:31:16.819 --> 01:31:18.124
- DON'T, MAN.
- OUT. OUT.

01:31:18.168 --> 01:31:20.344
JOEL, MAN, WHAT ARE YOU...?
HEY, MAN.

01:31:22.389 --> 01:31:24.435
JOEL, COME ON, MAN.

01:31:27.307 --> 01:31:29.962
WOW, WHAT A GODDAMN
PSYCHO.

01:31:36.273 --> 01:31:37.709
- SHELLEY.
- HI. WHERE'S LAINIE?

01:31:37.753 --> 01:31:39.232
SHE'S AT THE DANCE
WITH JOEL.

01:31:39.276 --> 01:31:42.061
NAH. NO, SHE LEFT.
JOEL HIT HER AND SHE LEFT.

01:31:42.105 --> 01:31:43.759
- WHAT? WHY?
- JOEL HIT HER?

01:31:43.802 --> 01:31:45.282
- YEAH.
- WHAT HAPPENED?

01:31:45.325 --> 01:31:48.415
I DON'T KNOW.
ALL I KNOW IS SHE'S WITH BOBBY

01:31:48.459 --> 01:31:50.461
AND IT'S PRETTY MUCH
ALL HIS FAULT.

01:31:50.505 --> 01:31:52.811
[ laughs ]
I FEEL SILLY.

01:31:52.855 --> 01:31:55.161
COME ON.
COME ON.

01:31:55.205 --> 01:31:57.381
YOU PROMISED ME YOU'D DO THIS.
JUST TRUST ME.

01:31:57.424 --> 01:31:59.426
- OKAY.
- TRUST ME.

01:32:01.559 --> 01:32:05.128
♪ HEY, SHOUT SUMMERTIME BLUES ♪

01:32:33.417 --> 01:32:36.246
♪ JIMMY DEAN ♪

01:32:47.866 --> 01:32:50.782
♪ HEY, KIDS, ROCK AND ROLL ♪

01:32:50.826 --> 01:32:53.742
♪ ROCK ON, OOH, MY SOUL ♪

01:32:53.785 --> 01:32:56.701
♪ HEY, KIDS, BOOGIE TOO ♪

01:32:56.745 --> 01:32:59.530
♪ DID YOU? ♪

01:32:59.574 --> 01:33:02.402
♪ HEY, SHOUT SUMMERTIME BLUES ♪

01:33:02.446 --> 01:33:05.188
♪ JUMP UP AND DOWN IN MY BLUE SUEDE SHOES ♪

01:33:05.231 --> 01:33:07.930
♪ HEY, KIDS, ROCK AND ROLL ♪

01:33:07.973 --> 01:33:10.280
♪ ROCK ON ♪

01:33:19.550 --> 01:33:23.206
- WHAT ARE YOU MORONS DOING?
- WHAT?

01:33:23.249 --> 01:33:26.165
- KELLER, WHERE'S THE CAR? COME ON, WE GOTTA GO NOW.
- NOT NOW.

01:33:26.209 --> 01:33:29.255
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, NOT NOW, BOBBY?
YOU STARTED THIS.

01:33:29.299 --> 01:33:31.736
- STARTED WHAT?
- JOEL'S GOING AFTER DUMAS.

01:33:31.780 --> 01:33:33.608
HE'S A BIG BOY.
HE CAN TAKE CARE OF HIMSELF.

01:33:33.651 --> 01:33:34.913
I'VE GOT THINGS
TO DO.

01:33:34.957 --> 01:33:36.872
OH, YOU HAVE
THINGS TO DO?

01:33:36.915 --> 01:33:38.874
GREAT, SO I SHIT
ON A FRIEND FOR YOU?

01:33:38.917 --> 01:33:40.571
FOR WHAT, BOBBY?
SO YOU CAN WALK AWAY?

01:33:40.615 --> 01:33:43.052
HE'S GOT A GUN.
HE'S GONNA KILL HIM.

01:33:43.095 --> 01:33:44.706
WE GOTTA GO.
I'LL TALK TO HIM.

01:33:44.749 --> 01:33:47.839
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN, LAINIE, YOU STAY HERE.
I'LL BE BACK.

01:33:47.883 --> 01:33:49.711
NO, I'M COMING
WITH YOU.

01:33:49.754 --> 01:33:52.627
♪ AND WHERE DO WE GO FROM HERE? ♪

01:33:54.759 --> 01:33:57.109
♪ WHICH IS THE WAY THAT'S CLEAR? ♪

01:33:57.153 --> 01:33:59.677
WAIT A MINUTE.
THERE SHE IS.

01:34:02.637 --> 01:34:04.595
- LAINIE, GET IN. YOU'RE GOING HOME.
- NO, MOTHER.

01:34:04.639 --> 01:34:07.598
I SAID, GET IN THE CAR. I'VE ALREADY
HEARD ABOUT THAT FIGHT YOU WERE IN.

01:34:07.642 --> 01:34:10.906
GET AWAY FROM HER. YOUNG MAN, I DON'T
WANT YOU TO SEE MY DAUGHTER ANYMORE.

01:34:10.949 --> 01:34:12.429
- LAINIE, GET IN THE CAR.
- RON, COULD YOU...?

01:34:12.472 --> 01:34:15.606
- HEY, STAY BACK.
- LET GO OF ME.

01:34:15.650 --> 01:34:17.608
ALL RIGHT,
LISTEN, LAINIE,

01:34:17.652 --> 01:34:20.002
GO HOME WITH THEM.
DON'T CAUSE A SCENE.

01:34:20.045 --> 01:34:21.525
I'M GONNA BE BY THE HOUSE LATER ON.

01:34:21.568 --> 01:34:23.396
NO, BOBBY, YOU WON'T BE
COMING BY LATER.

01:34:23.440 --> 01:34:25.398
I'LL BE BY.

01:34:25.442 --> 01:34:27.792
DON'T FALL ASLEEP.

01:34:28.880 --> 01:34:30.447
BE CAREFUL.

01:34:30.490 --> 01:34:32.492
Ron: COME ON, LAINIE, LET'S GO.

01:34:34.712 --> 01:34:37.149
♪ ROCK ON ♪

01:34:40.762 --> 01:34:42.764
♪ ROCK ON ♪

01:34:46.550 --> 01:34:48.508
♪ ROCK ON... ♪

01:34:48.552 --> 01:34:52.948
YO, DUMAS.
HEY, DUMAS.

01:34:52.991 --> 01:34:55.428
JOEL, JOEL.

01:34:55.472 --> 01:34:57.430
[ laughs ]

01:34:57.474 --> 01:34:59.955
ARE YOU HERE ALONE, JOEL?

01:34:59.998 --> 01:35:01.957
YEAH, I AM.

01:35:02.000 --> 01:35:04.133
NOW I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SMARTER THAN THAT.

01:35:04.176 --> 01:35:05.395
I AM.

01:35:05.438 --> 01:35:06.875
GUN!

01:35:06.918 --> 01:35:08.833
HEY! YO!

01:35:08.877 --> 01:35:11.227
WAIT A SECOND, BOYS.
MAN, IT'S A PARTY.

01:35:11.270 --> 01:35:12.837
WHO'S GOT THE CHIPS?

01:35:14.709 --> 01:35:17.015
LAINIE, IF THAT BOY COMES, I
DON'T WANT YOU TALKING TO HIM.

01:35:17.059 --> 01:35:19.017
YOU DON'T SAY.

01:35:19.061 --> 01:35:21.411
DAMN IT, I'M TIRED
OF THIS ATTITUDE.

01:35:21.454 --> 01:35:24.327
I'M SERIOUSLY CONSIDERING
MOVING US TO ANOTHER TOWN.

01:35:24.370 --> 01:35:25.894
THESE KIDS, AND
ESPECIALLY THAT BOY,

01:35:25.937 --> 01:35:27.896
ARE NOTHING
BUT A BAD INFLUENCE.

01:35:27.939 --> 01:35:29.898
I MEAN, LOOK AT THAT FIGHT
YOU HAD AT THE DANCE.

01:35:29.941 --> 01:35:32.639
NOW WHY DID YOU HAVE TO
PROVOKE JOEL LIKE THAT?

01:35:32.683 --> 01:35:34.337
YEAH, I PROVOKED JOEL.

01:35:34.380 --> 01:35:36.818
I WOULDN'T LET HIM SCREW ME
STANDING UP ON THE DANCE FLOOR.

01:35:36.861 --> 01:35:38.820
I SHOULD BE
COMMITTED FOR THAT.

01:35:38.863 --> 01:35:41.170
MOTHER, PLEASE.
I'D LOVE TO SEE YOU MOVE AWAY.

01:35:41.213 --> 01:35:43.259
DAMN IT, LAINIE,
NOT IN FRONT OF RON.

01:35:43.302 --> 01:35:45.087
OH, AND ANOTHER
THING, RON...

01:35:45.130 --> 01:35:47.393
I DON'T WANT YOU AND MY MOTHER
SEEING EACH OTHER ANYMORE.

01:35:55.184 --> 01:35:57.186
WHAT'S THAT?

01:36:00.711 --> 01:36:02.713
GIVE IT TO HER?

01:36:08.414 --> 01:36:10.373
I'M REALLY SORRY,
LAINIE.

01:36:10.416 --> 01:36:13.202
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU REALLY THINK,
